title: barbecued ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ribs, in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil.
Brown ribs and drain grease.
Pour sauce over ribs and bake in 300° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, uncovered!

title: wonderful salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate and serve or freeze and serve.
Good as chilled salad or served as frozen salad.

title: golden harvest muffins
directions: Line muffin pan with paper baking cups. Combine flours, sugar, soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Add apples, carrots, coconut, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Add oil, milk, vanilla and eggs. Stir just until moist.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 36 to 40 muffins.

title: poor man's lasagne
directions: Brown meat; add onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add oregano. Mix together cream of chicken soup, 1 can water and tomato sauce. Cook lasagne noodles.
Layer noodles and meat and soup mixture. Slice Velveeta cheese and put on top.
Cook about 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: beth lamphere's cheese grits
directions: Cook grits, water and salt by directions on the box.
Set aside.

title: green punch
directions: Mix sugar and 3 c. water and heat to dissolve; remove from heat stir in lime jello until dissolved. Add pineapple juice, juice from oranges and lemons; add entire bottle of almond extract and shake well. Serves 40.

title: hot apple spice drink
directions: Bring to a boil.
Then let simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: layered cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer the lettuce, cauliflower and carrot. Cover this with the salad dressing, making sure it is covered completely and airtight.
Top this with the layer of onion, bacon and Cheddar cheese, then sprinkle over this the 1/4 cup sugar. Cover tightly.
Do not put in plastic bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: cabbage en croute
directions: In a large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter. Add sugar and lemon juice. Stir until sugar dissolves. Add cabbage, apple, onion and salt.
Cook over medium heat 7 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally. Drain. Add sour cream and mix well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: You may add chopped nuts, raisins or maraschino cherries and/or small can drained crushed pineapple.

title: fancy pudding
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water; let stand until cool and partly set, then whip.
Mix in the nuts, marshmallows, cherries, coconut and salt.
Last, fold in the whipped cream.
Can be served in sponge cups or with ladyfingers.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Combine Crisco and sugar; cream well.
Add cocoa, salt, eggs and Milnot.
Mix together thoroughly.
Add flour and vanilla; mix well.
Add nuts; mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and drain cranberries.
Add water and cook until skins pop.
Add sugar and cook until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add dry Jell-O and stir until well dissolved.
Add pineapple and nuts and refrigerate until set.

title: berry delight
directions: In medium bowl, prepare gelatin according to package directions.
Spoon into oblong ovenproof dish and chill until gelatin has set.
Top with slices of cake.
In a medium bowl, prepare pudding as directed on package.
Spoon over cake slices and chill until pudding is set.
Spoon whipped topping over pudding, cover with plastic wrap or foil and refrigerate.
Cut into squares to serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix well and roll in 2 logs.
Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Slice when ready to bake.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Let cool on paper towel.

title: banana walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Spray 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan with nonstick vegetable spray. Puree bananas in mixing bowl with electric beater. Beat in eggs, sugar, butter and milk. Sift

in flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir with wooden spoon just to blended. Fold in nuts and flavoring. Spread evenly in loaf pan. Bake 60 minutes. Test for doneness by inserting a wooden pick in the center of loaf. Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Remove from pan and completely cool on a wire rack. Wrap air-tight. Store in the refrigerator. Makes 1 loaf.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a square Pyrex baking dish, layer vanilla wafers, then a layer of sliced bananas.
Make 3 to 4 layers according to depth of dish.
Beat milk, sugar and egg yolks (save egg whites for meringue).
Add flour to mixture and cook over low to medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add vanilla flavoring, then pour mixture over banana and vanilla wafers.
Make meringue by adding 1 tablespoon of sugar per egg white and beating until stiff.
Spoon over banana pudding and brown meringue under broiler of oven.

title: artichokes a la roquefort
directions: Melt butter and cheese, mixing well.
Cut artichokes in half or fourth if large.
Combine all ingredients and heat.
Serve in chafing dish.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar and egg.
Blend in vanilla, baking soda and salt.
Add flour and mix well.
Chill about one hour.
Roll out and cut into desired shapes.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Cream sugar, brown sugar, shortening and peanut butter until fluffy, then add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Then add flour, baking powder and salt.

title: nachos el pronto
directions: Open the can of chili and spread desired amount on each chip. Place chips on cookie sheet close together.
Sprinkle with grated cheese, used generously.
Top with all of the other ingredients and place under broiler until cheese is melted and starts to bubble. If you would like to use the microwave, cook for 45 seconds.
Make as much or as little as you like.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients except 1 cup croutons and the cheese.
Spoon into baking dish and sprinkle with remaining croutons and cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine applesauce, soda and shortening.
Add sugar and spices.
Add salt, flour, nuts, dates and raisins.
Bake in two loaf pans at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
For Christmas, add some candied cherries.

title: sausage delights
directions: With sausage and cheese at room temperature, grate cheese and combine all ingredients.
Roll in 1 inch balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: unleavened bread
directions: Add 3 cups flour to water.
Gradually add last cup until too stiff to stir.
Knead in remaining flour.
Knead about 20 minutes. Shape into loaf.
Put in oiled loaf pan.
Cover with damp cloth or towel.
Let rise in warm place for 24 hours.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken curry
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Then add the remaining ingredients and let simmer for flavors to blend.
This recipe can be cut in half or doubled and frozen.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash potatoes real well.
Add butter, evaporated milk, sugar and milk.
Heat ingredients.
Then add vanilla and lemon.
Add baking powder. Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
This makes 2 pies.

title: chip dip
directions: Cook egg, sugar and vinegar until thick.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: plesent mobley's banana nut bread
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar, then add the eggs, well beaten.
Add bananas, mixed with buttermilk and vanilla. Next, add flour, sifted with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add nuts and bake in any type loaf pan in moderate oven.

title: lemon jello dessert
directions: Make jello according to box directions.
When slightly thickened, add fruit.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
Top with dressing and sprinkle with pecans.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Add all other ingredients. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until soft ball stage, while stirring constantly.
Take off fire and add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and spread in buttered pan.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crackers and butter) well and place in a buttered dish.
Top with crushed cracker crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until crackers are browned.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Melt oleo in a heavy saucepan.
Stir in flour or cornstarch until smooth.
Add can of Carnation evaporated milk.
Add sugar and cook on low heat until thick.
Stir in cheese that has been grated on large hole side of grater.
Stir over heat until melted. Remove from heat and pour in mixing bowl.
Whip with a mixer until smooth.
Add pimento and mayonnaise; whip again until smooth.
Store in refrigerator in tightly covered container.
Will keep for 3 or 4 weeks.

title: wojapi(sioux indian fruit soup)
directions: Bring the juice to boil.
Add enough thickening to make the consistency of thin gravy.
Add sugar and pat of butter.
Delicious eaten with Indian fry bread.

title: pork parcels
directions: Cook rice.
Put into bowl.
Meanwhile, cook the corn and peas in boiling salted water for 2 minutes. Chop the onions.
Add to the rice and mix well together. Season to taste.
Cut 4 large squares of aluminum foil.
Put a chop on each piece.
Sprinkle well with soy sauce.
Put 1/4 of the mixture on top of each chop. Add a spoonful of cider.
Wrap into a parcel and place on a pan. Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 4.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine in heavy pan. Add sugar, syrup and milk. Bring to a boil and cook to 227°. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and pecans. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut into squares when cool.

title: enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in hot oil until they are translucent. Add garlic, hot sauce and beef. Heat through. Salt and pepper. Heat oven to 350. Take one shell, place 1/8 of mixture on shell, 1/8 of dirty rice and 1/8 cheese. Roll, tuck in ends and place seam side down in a 9x13 casserole dish. Cover with tomato sauce. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: georgia's baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Can also make in slow cooker for 2 to 3 hours.

title: noodles
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add salt and milk.
Stir in as much flour as needed to make mixture hold or until it cleans bowl.
Turn out on floured surface.
Knead a few times.
Roll out as thin as possible. The thinner the better.
Use plenty of flour to prevent sticking to surface.
Let stand for 2 hours or so.
Cut into noodles.
Cook in boiling broth or let dry completely and store in freezer in freezer bags.

title: fried squash
directions: Place sliced squash in large bowl with lid.
Add salt, pepper and 1/2 to 1 cup flour.
Shake bowl to coat the squash.
Place in the refrigerator for 1/2 hour or overnight.
Drain excess liquid from bowl.
Place squash slices in hot grease and fry.
`Best flavor results from bacon drippings.
Serve browned and piping hot.

title: caramel apple coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy; gradually add sugar. Blend in oil and vanilla. Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Add to egg mixture. Stir in apples and pecans.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until the cake tests done. Cool in pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes. Remove cake to a serving platter.
Make topping.

title: mamma's pepper jelly
directions: Place peppers and vinegar into a blender container.
Chop to medium-fine consistency.
Pour into large stainless steel boiler. Add sugar, stirring to mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
(Watch carefully to prevent mixture from boiling over.)
Remove from heat.
Strain through a large stainless steel strainer.
Return to a boil; boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add Certo and a drop or two of red or green food coloring, if desired.
Pour jelly into sterilized jars and seal.
Give jelly as gifts or serve as a spread with cream cheese and crackers.
Makes 6 (1/2 pint) jars.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: best corn bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix dressing (dry mix), tuna and cream cheese together. Roll over chopped pecans until covered well. Chill until firm. Serve with crackers.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into patties and fry.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello in hot water.
Add ice cubes and stir until melted. Add blueberries (reserve some to color cream cheese, if desired). Add nuts. May also add some pineapple, if desired.
Put half of this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When firm, spread cream cheese over the top.
Cover with remaining half of jello mixture.

title: hot spiced pineapple juice
directions: Heat pineapple juice and cinnamon for 10 minutes.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Remove cinnamon and serve hot.
Yield: 2 1/2 cups.

title: 15 bean over ginger rice medley
directions: Boil beans for 2 hours with bacon grease to package directions. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 more minutes. Add flavor package. Remove from heat.
Prepare a 4-cup finished serving rate of white rice, adding 1 tablespoon curry powder to rice as it cooks.
Serve 15 bean over ginger rice.
Salt to taste.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Do not dilute soup.

title: herbed boursin(cheese balls)
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Roll in ball and cover with lemon pepper.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: georgie's pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions in food processor.
Put in large pot and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain. Cover again with boiling water.
Bring this to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Drain dry.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 15 minutes. Pour into hot sterilized jars. Seal.

title: mexican-style pot roast
directions: In 8-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat in oil, cook the halved garlic cloves until lightly browned; discard garlic cloves. Add beef chuck arm roast and cook in these drippings until browned on all sides.
Remove the meat to plate and set aside.
In same Dutch oven pan in drippings over medium heat, cook hot peppers and onions until tender, stirring frequently.
Return meat to pan; add tomato puree, vinegar, sugar, salt and oregano; over high heat, heat until boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add the quartered green peppers; cover and simmer 1 hour longer or until meat is fork-tender and skim off the fat from juices remaining in pan.
Add the corn to the meat mixture over high heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until kernels of corn are tender.
Makes 12 servings.

title: rhubarb custard pie(good)
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour, milk and nutmeg; add rhubarb.
Place in pie shell; add butter.
Top with top pastry.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° until pie is bubbly all over and crust is well browned.

title: sea leg salad
directions: Boil noodles; drain and rinse in cold water.
Add in other ingredients along with mayonnaise until consistency desired.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Blend last items in and chill if desired.
Drop or form into balls size of walnut.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Flatten to 1/4 inch thick.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes in 375° oven.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes; drain off liquid.
Add chopped onion, egg, flour, salt and pepper.
Drop by tablespoonful into 1/4 inch of hot shortening in skillet.
Pan-fry about 3 minutes on each side; turn only when well browned.
Yields 12 pancakes.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Mix together in heavy saucepan and bring to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Set off stove and add vanilla, peanut butter and raw oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper and let set.

title: peanut butter and jelly bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, baking powder and sugar in large bowl until well blended. Cut in butter until coarse crumbs form.
Beat eggs and vanilla with a fork in small bowl until foamy; stir into flour mixture until well blended.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion in margarine until golden.
Combine soup, water and cheese.
Thaw broccoli.
Prepare rice and set aside.
Combine all ingredients and place in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Grease 2 pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch).
Coat with cornmeal.
Mix 3 cups of flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda in a big bowl. Mix milk and water in saucepan and warm to 105°.
Stir into flour mix and stir in remaining flour.
Put in pans; sprinkle top with remaining cornmeal.
Let rise to double.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter together in microwave.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in buttered pan and refrigerate.

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Generously grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Set aside.
Blend sugar, corn syrup, Crisco and vanilla in large saucepan.
Cook on medium-high heat about 2 minutes or until light and foamy, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add popcorn, tossing to coat.
Stir in peanuts.
Spread in greased baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 8 minutes.
Use pancake turner to push popcorn from bottom of pan.
Turn and stir well.
Return to oven for 7 additional minutes.
Use turner again to turn and stir. Cool in pan.
Break into bite-size pieces.
Store in covered container.

title: corn pudding(original recipe)
directions: Add frozen corn to remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oatmeal, chips, M&M's and baking soda in a large pan.
Mix corn syrup, eggs, vanilla, peanut butter and margarine. Combine the 2 mixtures (use hands if needed).
Roll into balls about the size of a walnut.
Flatten.
M&M's may be placed on top if you want a monster face.

title: beef casserole with water chestnuts
directions: Saute meat with onion and garlic.
Drain off fat.

title: baked wheaty chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Mix crumbs and add seasonings in medium size bowl.
Melt oleo in medium size bowl.
Dip chicken in oleo and roll in the crumbs and place in baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
If not brown on top, place under broiler for a few minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese straws or pennies
directions: Cream butter and cheese until smooth, add flour and pepper; blend thoroughly.
Use cookie press to make straws or roll into balls and flatten with thumb.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a bowl. Beat the egg and milk and add to dry ingredients. Drop from a teaspoon into hot chicken gravy. Cover, cook 10 to 12 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
Scald milk and water in a double boiler.
Add sugar and flour mixture.
Over medium heat, cook slightly.
Remove 1/2 cup of mixture and add beaten egg yolks; mix and cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and 1/2 can coconut.
Blend and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with rest of coconut.

title: hamburger cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add relish, picante sauce and meat mixture.
Keep warm in crock-pot.

title: butter pecan turtle bars
directions: Mix crust with electric mixer at medium speed until particles are fine.
Pat firmly into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup coarsely chopped pecans evenly over crust.

title: cucumber and cider salad
directions: Peel cucumbers; cut them in half
lengthwise
and scoop out the seeds with a spoon.
Thinly
slice
cucumbers
and put into a bowl.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and let stand for 1 hour or until sugar is dissolved. Add the eggs, then the vanilla. Mix together the flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg. Add the pecans. Combine the two mixtures.
Mix to moisten. Bake in well-greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or 2 loaf pans for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: * banana surprise *
directions: Slice bananas lengthwise, but not all the way through.
In the center of the bananas, fill with pieces of chocolate and the marshmallows.
Wrap in foil and bake in hot coals or in 350° oven until chocolate melts.
These are messy, but good.

title: meat loaf sauce
directions: Mix the soup and the puree.
Heat until well blended.
Serve over meat loaf to make it more spicy and attractive.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together Veg-All, peas, mayonnaise, onion, Cheddar cheese and water chestnuts.
Use cooking spray to grease casserole dish (I use a pie plate).
Pour Veg-All mixture into dish.
Cover with crackers and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cover chicken with water in large pan; add the bouillon cubes. Simmer until chicken is tender.
Debone chicken.
Reserve 4 cups broth.
Cook spaghetti in broth; don't drain.
Saute onions and peppers in oleo on low heat until tender.
Don't brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes, uncovered.

title: artichoke and radicchio salad
directions: Cook frozen artichoke hearts according to package directions. If using canned artichokes, rinse with cold water and drain. In a bowl with artichokes add 1 tablespoon olive oil and 1 teaspoon lemon juice; let stand for 15 minutes.
Add radicchio, basil and remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil; toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon lemon juice; toss.
Divide salad between 2 plates; grate Parmesan cheese generously on top.

title: chunky chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the chicken breasts, stuffing mix and melted margarine.
Dip chicken in mixture.
Roll in stuffing mix.
Place in greased casserole.
Pour 1/2 cup melted margarine over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: beer chicken
directions: Combine butter, beer, lemon juice, garlic and lemon pepper. Pour over chicken.
Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours.
Brush over chicken while cooking.

title: poppy seed quick bread("slightly sweet breakfast bread.")
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Beat together eggs, sugar, half and half and the oil.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually stir flour mixture into eggs.
Stir in poppy seed.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pan. Turn out onto a rack.

title: jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in 6-quart Dutch oven over moderately high heat for 1 minute.
Add chicken and sausage and brown for 6 to 7 minutes on each side.
Transfer to plate and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add onion to Dutch oven and saute, stirring frequently until soft (5 minutes).
Add celery and green peppers and saute 5 more minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, ham, garlic, bay leaf, paprika, thyme, salt and red pepper.
Add chicken and sausage.
Cover.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in rice and water; cover and cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: moma's terrific lasagna
directions: Boil noodles as directed on box.
Mix sauces and meats together.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours or until rice is done in 350°
oven.

title: crunchy hot crab bites
directions: Preheat broiler.
Combine crab, lime juice, lime peel, green onion, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and hot pepper sauce.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
Brush melted butter on toast rounds and arrange in a single layer in a broiler pan.
Top each round with a portion of the crab mixture, then with 1 1/2 teaspoons cheese.
Broil until cheese is melted and crab mixture is hot.

title: strawberry cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 9x13x2 inch baking pan. In large bowl, combine cake mix, pecans, butter and 1 of the eggs. Mix well and press into pan. In medium bowl, combine the remaining egg with the confectioners' sugar, cream cheese and strawberry preserves. Beat until smooth. Pour over the strawberry "crust". Bake for 45 minutes, until cheesecake topping is set and is lightly browned. Allow to cool completely before slicing. Cut into 1x2-inch bars.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
Brown ground beef.
Add Italian seasoning.
In a large bowl, add cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Mix the ingredients.
Layer the noodles and mixture out, then sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Cut cheese into small cubes and add Ro-Tel. Cook in microwave until cheese is melted.
Mix. Cook hamburger meat and drain.
Mix cheese and Ro-Tel mixture, hamburger meat, drained corn, taco seasoning and milk.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: watermelon cool pie
directions: Combine boiling water and watermelon jello until dissolved. In separate bowl, combine cold water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups. Stir in gelatin until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.

title: vegetable bean soup
directions: Place beans in a large pot and cover with water 2 inches above beans.
Soak 8 hours or overnight.
Drain beans and return to pot. Add chicken broth, water, onions, carrots, celery, garlic, parsley flakes, basil, oregano and pepper.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add spinach and cook 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
If desired, sprinkle each serving with Parmesan cheese.
Makes about 1 gallon or 10 to 12 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar;
add
remaining ingredients. Cook at 350°.
For
2 dozen cupcakes, cook for 25 minutes; 8 x 13-inch pan, cook
for
45	minutes; 1 loaf and 1 muffin, cook for 30 minutes.
Check with a toothpick for doneness.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients. Fold in the whipped topping.
Spoon into pie crust. Chill.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk
and cocoa in a saucepan. cook over medium heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts and blend thoroughly.
Add oatmeal and blend thoroughly. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Do not bake.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: diabetic apple crunch
directions: Place the sliced apples in a 1-quart casserole.
Combine the orange juice, Sweet 'N Low, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Pour over apples and toss.
Combine the graham cracker crumbs with the melted butter; sprinkle over apples.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend sugar, eggs and oil well, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer 1/2 of chicken on bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish.
Then add layer of dressing.
Add layer of celery soup, another layer of chicken and layer of mushroom soup.
Repeat layers, ending with dressing and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: smoky sausage crescents
directions: Soften cream cheese.
In mixer bowl, beat the cream cheese on medium speed of electric mixer about 2 minutes. Add mustard and horseradish. Beat until fluffy. Separate roll dough into triangles.

Cut each triangle in half to make 16 smaller triangles. Spread the first 2-inches of base of each triangle with 1 teaspoon of cream cheese mixture. Add a sausage. Beginning with base, roll dough around the sausage.
Place, seam side down, on greased baking sheet.
Bake in a
400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 16.

title: nut chocolate drops
directions: Preheat oven to 400° for 10 minutes.
Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Melt chocolate with buttermilk.
Add to blended ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoonful.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Cook grits and while still cooking, add eggs, cheese, butter and seasoning.
Place in buttered baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Can be made the night before and refrigerated.
Serves 12.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in the shortening and butter.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla and add to flour mixture.
Chill 1 hour.

title: applesauce pie
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar, beaten eggs, applesauce and cinnamon. Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° until done.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix onion soup, apricot preserves, and russian dressing well. Coat chicken breast and bake at 350° until chicken is done.

title: mustard greens and pork strips
directions: Put enough water in large Dutch oven to cover ingredients. Heat to boil.
Lower heat and simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with corn bread.

title: imagination cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the coconut.
Shape in very small balls and roll in coconut.
Makes approximately 50 balls.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs, milk, salt, mustard and peppers.
Put croutons in bottom of baking dish.
Layer sausage and egg mixture; top with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough out on a floured surface into a 13-inch circle.
Transfer to a 12-inch pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Fold over and crimp an edge around the pizza, making it fit the pan. Bake according to the cookie dough package directions. Undercook it a little to avoid brittleness.
Mix cream cheese and sugar and spread on cooled cookie.
Arrange fruit in a pleasing pattern on top.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, milk, beaten eggs, salt, soda, bacon drippings and corn.
Mix well and set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain well.
Pour half of batter into well-greased cast-iron skillet that has been dusted with cornmeal.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over batter.
Sprinkle meat over cheese.
Sprinkle chopped onion and jalapenos evenly over meat.
Top with remaining batter and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion.
Add Nature's Seasons and garlic.
Rinse when no longer pink in colander under hot water. Put in crock-pot, along with canned beans, taco mix and green chiles.
Add tomato sauce to taste.
(It's hot; you may want to start with about 2 ounces.)
Cover; cook on low all day.

title: fruit and nut loaf
directions: Set oven at 375° to preheat.
Sift together in large mixing bowl, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and beat on medium speed until mixed, about 1/2 minute.
Turn into greased 9 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand about 20 minutes before baking.
Bake about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Turn out of pan. Cool on cake rack.
Slices better 1 day old.

title: italian style cauliflower
directions: Remove large outer leaves of cauliflower; break cauliflower into flowerets.
Arrange in a steaming rack.
Place over boiling water.
Cover and steam 5 to 8 minutes to desired tenderness. Transfer to a serving bowl, keep warm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt oleo in water and add dressing mix. Toss lightly but not well. Place 1/2 mix in greased casserole (13 x 9 x 2). Mix chicken, onion, celery, salt and mayonnaise and spread over dressing in casserole. Cover with remaining 1/2 dressing mix. Beat eggs. Add milk and pour over the top. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove 1 hour before baking. Spread undiluted soup over top. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over top; it will melt.

title: willie mae's angel biscuits
directions: Blend shortening and sift flour until crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Roll out on floured board and cut or pat to desired size by hand.
Remaining dough may be covered in a bowl and kept in the refrigerator for several days and used as needed. Bake biscuits at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yields 36.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan. Add sugar and egg.
Mix well, then pour over apples that have been put into
pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna and noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directions allow.
Layer noodles with tuna and cream of mushroom soup twice.
Put crushed potato chips on top. Put milk in dish to avoid sticking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour and serve.

title: crab soup
directions: Cook in crock-pot for 5 to 6 hours.

title: special k candy
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to just a rapid boil (no more). Take from heat. Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well, then add Special K and mix. Drop with teaspoon or make a small ball.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper in small bowl; mix well.
Microwave broccoli using package directions; drain.
Layer half the broccoli, half the soup mixture and half the onions in greased 6 x 10-inch glass baking dish.
Add layers of remaining broccoli and soup mixture.
Microwave, covered, with waxed paper on High for 8 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Microwave for 1 minute longer.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Melt oleo in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer 3/4 of potatoes.
Mix rest of ingredients in large bowl and pour into pan on top of the hash browns.
Sprinkle rest of potatoes on top of egg mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with coffee, orange juice and toast for a complete breakfast.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: In skillet, cook sausage and onion until brown.
Add sauerkraut, well drained and chopped fine, and 2 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Combine cream cheese, parsley, mustard, garlic, salt and pepper.
Stir into kraut mixture.
Shape into 30 (3/4-inch) balls and coat with flour.
Combine eggs and milk.
Roll floured balls in egg mixture and then in crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet; cover with foil and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: new york strip steak florentine
directions: *Slice garlic paper thin with a single-edged razor blade or crush and chop fine.

title: how to preserve children
directions: Put noodles in a pot of water.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Get sauce from the store.
Put sauce on the noodles and eat.

title: little party wieners
directions: Wrap wieners with bacon pieces and put a toothpick through each.
Place in crock-pot and pour brown sugar over wieners.
Cook for 4 hours on low.

title: zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Add a little oil to frying pan.
Add vegetables and cook on medium low until tender.
You can also add onions, pea pods or whatever other vegies you like.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cabbage leaves, bacon and tomato paste.
Roll mixture in cabbage leaves.
Place rolled cabbage in skillet lined with sliced bacon on bottom.
Spread the tomato paste on top.
Cover with tight lid; cook over low heat for about 2 hours.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to the directions on the box.
Drain. Let cool or cool in cold water.
Put spaghetti in a large mixing bowl. Slice vegetables and add to noodles as in a regular salad. Add Zesty Italian dressing as desired and sprinkle with Salad Supreme.
Mix well.

title: christmas carrot cake
directions: Sift flour with baking soda, powder, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Mix sugar with oil, beating well.
Alternately add eggs with flour mixture to sugar.
Fold in carrots, dates, nuts and raisins.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top springs back.
Let cool on rack 10 minutes.
Loosen around sides and center.
Remove from pan; cool. When cool, you can frost with cream cheese frosting or leave plain.

title: mushroom burgers with gravy
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Shape into 9 burgers.
Heat frypan with olive oil.
Cook and brown burgers.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Slice rolls lengthwise through center.
Add a layer of ham and cheese and put on bottom layer of rolls with ham and cheese back into the foil pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the rolls in the pan.
Leave uncovered until the butter sets.
Put top layer of rolls on and cover with foil.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. May be made ahead of time and refrigerated for 3 to 5 days before baking!

title: baklava
directions: Place sheets of phyllo pastry in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, brushing each second sheet with melted butter.
When 10 sheets are in place, combine nuts and sugar; spread 1/2 over top sheet.
Place another 5 sheets of buttered phyllo on top and sprinkle with nut mixture. Repeat and end with buttered phyllo sheets.
With sharp knife, cut baklava into diamond shaped pieces.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Reduce temperature to 300° and bake 45 minutes more.
Cool and pour hot syrup over top.
Serves 24.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain 1 cup blueberry juice; drain pineapple and add boiling water to jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add blueberry juice and fruit.
Chill until firm.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a long baking pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a medium bowl; mix well.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine egg and milk; add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: bow tie pasta
directions: Saute garlic in oil.
Add chicken, broccoli and tomatoes; saute 5 minutes.
Add basil, red pepper flakes, wine and broth. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add cooked pasta and sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.

title: pumpkin bread with caramel glaze
directions: Combine the ingredients; mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift first 2 ingredients together; set aside.
Bring next four ingredients to a boil.
Pour over flour/sugar mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and soda; beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put all of these in blender except nuts.

title: coconut cream banana dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and sugar.
Put into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Beat powdered sugar with cream cheese.
Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Slice bananas over filling.
Mix pudding.
Place on top of bananas. Spread remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with ground nuts.

title: mrs. conley's pot pie(very good)
directions: Mix all together and roll out like dumplings.
Put in chicken broth and cook for 20 minutes, covered.
Do not stir while cooking.

title: beef and noodles au gratin(weight watchers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: pretzel salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put first 3 ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes; let cool.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar, pineapple and Cool Whip.
After baked pretzels have cooled, add to cream cheese mixture.
Serve immediately (pretzels get soft if not served within an hour or so).

title: polish potato dumplings
directions: Drain liquid from potatoes.
Add eggs, salt and flour; mix well with wooden spoon.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into 2 quarts boiling, salted water.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook in large iron skillet the milk, dates, sugar, syrup, salt and oleo to a soft ball stage.
Add vanilla and beat until thick. Add nuts.
Continue beating until it can be poured on a wet cloth and rolled.
Makes 2 nice size rolls.
Slice to serve.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken to bite size pieces.
Crumble bacon.
Wash and drain lettuce.
Layer all ingredients in bowl, starting with lettuce, then chicken, bacon, water chestnuts and cheese.
Apply dressing as desired.
Serves approximately 6.

title: applesauce pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in applesauce and pumpkin.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with apple juice. Stir in nuts.
Turn batter into two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until done.
Makes two loaves.

title: tomato mozzarella salad
directions: Slice tomatoes and Mozzarella.
On a large platter, alternate tomato, Mozzarella, tomato and Mozzarella until ingredients are used.
Mix next 6 ingredients.
Pour over tomatoes and Mozzarella. Sprinkle basil and onions over tomatoes and Mozzarella.

title: bean dip
directions: Crumble beef into 9-inch round baking dish.
Stir in 1/2 cup onion and chili powder.
Microwave on High for 5 to 8 minutes or until beef is no longer pink, stirring once to break apart.
Stir in beans, salt and catsup. Cook on Medium in microwave for 7 to 10 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with remaining onion, olives and cheese; microwave until cheese melts and serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring milk and sugar to a boil.
Mix rest of ingredients to boiled mixture.
Place teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until hard.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Use a blender to crush tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Mix all together and add the next 6 ingredients.
Cook for 1 hour.
Then add tomato paste and bring to a boil.
Place in clean jars and seal with lids.

title: massie's pumpkin cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour 3 times.
Add dry ingredients.
Add pumpkin and flour alternately with pecans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Place pretzels in large covered bowl. Mix remaining in small bowl. Pour over pretzels. Cover bowl and shake every 30 minutes for several hours.

title: grandma b's chocolate spritz
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then beat in the egg.
Then beat in chocolate, vanilla and milk.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add to mixture; mix well.
Chill dough and shape.

title: old fashioned chili-mac
directions: Break spaghetti into small pieces.
Boil in salted water until tender.
Saute ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Open cans and pour chili and beans into a large, heavy pot.
Heat.
Pour off water on spaghetti and add to chili mixture.
Drain fat from ground beef mixture and add to chili; mix well.
Season to taste with hot sauce and chili powder.
Good.

title: jello pie
directions: Combine juice, sugar and jello in saucepan and bring to a boil. Set aside to cool.
Chill.
Whip 1 can Pet milk until stiff; add jello mixture and stir thoroughly.
Pour into crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: german chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt
chocolate
and
butter
in small saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Bring sugar and corn syrup
to
boil
in
separate
saucepans
over high heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Reduce heat and boil gently 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate mixture, pour slowly over eggs, stirring constantly. Stir in vanilla
and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes,
or
until
filling
is completely puffed across top. Cool and garnish with Coffee Topping.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and onions until tender; add cheese, milk and soup.
Mix well.
Pour in a casserole and sprinkle with crackers. Cut butter in small pieces and place on crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add apple slices on top and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Serve with milk or cream. Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare Minute rice as directed on box.
Cook broccoli; add to rice, soup and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute the onion and green pepper in the oil until soft.
Add ground beef and seasonings, stirring until brown.
Stir in cooked rice, tomatoes, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix thoroughly. Put in casserole dish.
Top with Velveeta cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken in an 8 x 12 x 2-inch dish.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and milk; stir well.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Cover and bake for 50 minutes.

title: vanilla sour cream pie
directions: Beat sour cream and milk with hand mixer until smooth.
Blend in pudding until smooth and slightly thickened.
Pour into crust and chill at least for 1 hour or until set.
If desired, serve with sweetened whipped cream.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine, and sugar.
Spray a 9 x 13 baking dish with non-stick spray and press pretzel mixture into the bottom.
Bake at 400° for 18-20 minutes.
Cool.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix well.
Marinate (at least 24 hours) in refrigerator, then serve.
Will keep for a long time.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain, then add onion and bell pepper until tender.
Next, add the remaining ingredients. Cook on medium heat for 25 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix
together
the
flour, cocoa, soda, sugar and salt. Make 3 holes and pour in mixture of vinegar, vanilla and oil. Pour water over the top and mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: bull's eye eggs
directions: Butter both sides of the bread. Using a small juice glass or 2-inch round cookie cutter, cut a hole in the center of the bread. Place the bread with the hole, and the hole, in a large skillet. Carefully crack the egg into the hole. Cook over medium heat until done on one side and then flip over and cook on the other side. It is like an over easy egg.
The hole can be used as toast.

title: chicken and pasta dinner for four
directions: Spray pan with Pam; add chicken and cook through.
Set aside.

title: creamy mac and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni, following directions on box.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; cook, stirring constantly until mixture is thick.
Stir in 1 cup cheese until melted.
Combine cheese mixture and macaroni.
Fold in remaining cheese.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole.
Combine crumbs and melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, onion, crushed noodles, salt, pepper and egg. Mix and shape into balls.
Brown in hot oil.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Add sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar, water and pineapple syrup to browned meatballs.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Add green peppers and pineapple.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over chow mein noodles.
Can be served over hot rice as well.

title: fun in the sun
directions: Prepare pudding with milk as directed on package.
Spoon into crusts.
Shortly before serving, put jelly bean sunglasses in place.
Cut licorice string for side pieces and add.
Cut a curved piece of licorice for mouth.
Put candy corn points facing out around face for rays.

title: autumn fruit cake
directions: Cream
margarine,
sugar
and eggs.
Add graham cracker crumbs and
baking powder.
Mix well.
Add coconut, pineapple, dried fruit,
nuts and flavoring (vanilla).
Mix well and bake in tube pan
sprayed
with a nonstick oil.	Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; knead into ball.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Warm dough by room temperature.
Roll dough on sugar or flour.
Use cookie cutters of choice.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tropical punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze and set out about 2 hours before serving.
It's better if you stir the punch while freezing.
Serve with cold Sprite.

title: chicken casserole with spaghetti
directions: Make white sauce by melting margarine, add flour and milk. Cook spaghetti in boiling water with bouillon until done; drain. Combine white sauce, spaghetti and chicken.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: vegetable aspic
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; add boiling water and mix well. Add salt, sugar, lemon juice and vinegar.
Cool until almost set (this doesn't take too long).
Fold in the chopped vegetables. Pour into mold; chill until set.
Serves 12 to 15 or does keep well in refrigerator for a week.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: Beat 1 egg, beat in 1/3 cup peanut butter.
Stir in salt, vanilla, butter and confectioners sugar.
Mix well.
Stir in another cup of confectioners sugar.
Shape into small balls and roll each ball in 3/4 cup of chopped, salted nuts.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Make sure margarine is softened well, then cream for 1 minute before gradually adding the sugar.
(The secret is that the margarine and sugar be creamed well.)
Melt the unsweetened chocolate and add it and the vanilla to the mixture; mix well. Add first egg and mix for 4 minutes.
Add the other egg and mix for 5 more minutes.
Pour into the pie shell and chill for 8 hours.
Top with Cool Whip
and garnish with chocolate shavings. (Hershey bars make good shavings),

title: skilletburgers(sloppy joes)
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender, but not brown.
Add tomato sauce, condensed soup, hot pepper sauce, salt and chili powder.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Spoon onto split toasted hamburger buns.

title: hello dollies
directions: In a 9 X 13 glass baking dish, melt butter.
Sprinkle a layer of graham crackers (do not mash) over bottom of pan.
Layer chocolate chips.
Layer nuts.
Layer shredded coconut.
Pour condensed milk over layers (do not stir).
Bake 300 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes, depending on oven (coconut should be a toasty brown).

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar.
Add vinegar and beet juice.
Cook over moderate flame until begins to get thick.
(Not too thick.) Add beets and margarine and heat until beets are hot.
This is delicious.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in water to which 1 teaspoon salt has been added; drain, let cool and add other ingredients.

title: cheese-krispies
directions: Combine all ingredients together; form in small balls.
Press with fork.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Add oats.
Mix egg with buttermilk; add to dry ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Add shortening.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil oleo, sugar and Karo for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add soda. Pour over corn.
Put in two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir after first 1/2 hour.

title: elaine solez fruitcake
directions: In a large mixing bowl sift the flour and salt over the pecans and raisins.
Mix thoroughly and set aside.
In another large bowl cream butter and sugar and add egg yolks, 1 at a time, stirring thoroughly.
Blend soda and water and stir it thoroughly into butter.
Stir in the Grand Marnier.
Pour this batter into the raisin/nut mixture and blend thoroughly, using hands if necessary, until all the flour is worked into the batter.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold them into the batter until no white shows. Spoon and scrape the mixture into a buttered and floured angel food cake pan.
Bake at 275° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours (test with toothpick). Cool a bit before removing from pan.
When cooled to room temperature, wrap cake in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 10 days.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well. In a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, place everything in order listed. Repeat layers, ending with cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: family dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to other ingredients and mix until well blended.
Cover and let rise 45 minutes.
Punch down and dip by spoonfuls into greased muffin pans.
Let rise again and then bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 10 to 12 rolls.

title: reese's peanut butter pie
directions: Combine the cream cheese, powdered sugar, milk and peanut butter.
Fold together with the Cool Whip.
Place in graham cracker crusts (chocolate or regular).
Freeze.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberry sauce in pan.
Add 1 cup water.
Bring to boil. Stir until completely dissolved.
Add Jell-0.
Let cool and add pineapple, strawberries and nuts.
Makes 9 to 10 servings.

title: orange slice roll
directions: Crunch vanilla wafers up in food processor or with rolling pin, then add remaining ingredients.
Makes 4 long rolls, then roll in powdered sugar or ground nuts.
Put in refrigerator and cool.
Slice as desired.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown together bacon and hamburg.
Drain off grease.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours, depending on thickness desired.

title: honey chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and honey.
Add beaten eggs, melted chocolate and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet, which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan while still warm.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Scoop out bread.
Save for dipping.
Beat together all other ingredients.
Fill scooped out bread.
Wrap in 4 to 5 layers of foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fresh fruit torte
directions: Cut pound cake horizontally in three layers.
Set aside.

title: root beer
directions: Put in 2
gallon jars.
Cover and set in sun for 4 hours. Chill before serving.
Ready to serve the next day.
No need to bottle.

title: frioles(beans)
directions: Rinse and pick over beans and place them in a large stock pot. Add enough cold water to cover the beans.
Add half of the onions, half of the garlic, bay leaves and red pepper.
Cover; bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Add 4 tablespoons oil and salt, stirring to mix well.
Cover and continue cooking until beans are soft.
Add more water as necessary.
Uncover and cook another 30 minutes.

title: peppered rib-eye rub
directions: Substitution:
Two and one-half teaspoons Hot Shot for pepper and ground red pepper.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; mix in flour on slow speed.
Put in pan (2 x 10 x 14-inch).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Score in pan before baking.
Sprinkle sugar on top.

title: shrimp and sausage rice
directions: Mix all ingredients
and
place
in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for
to 25 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all except stuffing and cheese.
Put into 9 x 13-inch casserole and cover with stuffing and cheese.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour.
Parboil cauliflower.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beginning with rice, layer the ingredients and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: italian soup
directions: Pour water in large cooking pot.
Add carrots, cracked wheat, potatoes, celery, onions, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Let this cook while you saute the meat and drain.
Add meat and the rest of the vegetables.
Simmer together to combine flavors. Serve with cheese crackers.

title: german sour cream twists
directions: Sift flour and salt into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water (110 - 115°).
Stir into flour mixture with sour cream, eggs, and vanilla extract.
Mix thoroughly with hand. Scrape dough down from sides of bowl to center.
Cover bowl with damp cloth and set in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
(The dough does not rise but becomes very cold and rather firm.)

title: taco soup
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and heat well (may add water). Add remaining ingredients (optional) when you eat the dish, not when you're cooking it.

title: instant miracle rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast; mix.
Place desired amount on floured board.
Roll out and cut as for biscuits.
Let warm to room temperature before baking 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Dough will keep several weeks in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: raisin honey cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add honey and eggs; beat until well blended.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt.
Stir into honey mixture; mix well. Fold in raisins and nuts.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Flatten slightly. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: tomato-pineapple relish
directions: Scald, peel and chop the tomatoes.
Bring quickly to a boil and simmer, stirring, for 10 minutes.
Measure 2 cups into large saucepan.
Add all ingredients except pectin and bring to a full rolling boil. Boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in pectin.
Skim off foam. Continue to stir and skim for 5 minutes.
Ladle into hold jars and seal.
Great on roast pork.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Heat 1 c. of the juice.
Add Jello stirring until dissolved. Add remaining juice, salt, Tabasco, sugar, onion, celery and shrimp.
Pour into individual molds.
Chill over night for best results.

title: potato casserole
directions: Brown potatoes and onion in butter.
Put in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: velma's texas brunch
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cube bread in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish; top with Cheddar cheese, then top with browned sausage.
Mix together 4 eggs, mustard and 2 cups milk and pour over sausage and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, pour a can of mushroom soup mixed well with 1 cup milk and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can cook less with higher temperature.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cream puffs
directions: Mix water, salt and margarine and bring to a boil.
Add flour, then
add
eggs, one at a time, stirring well.
Bake on ungreased cookie
sheet.
Drop by spoon 2 inches apart.
Bake at 425°
for 15
minutes.
Cut
down
to 350° for 20 minutes. Cool; slice the sides 1/2 way through.
Mix vanilla pudding by directions
on box.
Fill puffs with pudding.
Close back and put icing on top.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil meat separately; chop.
Grind chicken skins.
Soak beans overnight.
Cook beans and onions in broth; mash.
Boil potatoes in jackets.
Mash tomatoes.
Add meat and broth.
Combine all ingredients except potatoes.
Mash potatoes.
Add to stew while hot.
Cook, stirring, to keep from sticking until thoroughly heated.
May be canned or frozen.
Yield: 13 quarts stew.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix egg yolks (set aside egg whites to be used later), butter and sugar.
Add juice from the lemons.
Add flour and milk.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture last.
Gently pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Middle should be firm. Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: beef and cabbage meal
directions: Remove outer leaves of cabbage, cut cabbage into 6 wedges. Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle onion and rice between wedges. Crumble ground beef between wedges.
Combine tomatoes, water, salt and pepper in bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 6 servings.
Total fat grams:

title: cheese-sausage appetizers
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine cheese, butter, flour, salt and pepper.
Beat with electric mixer on medium-low speed.
Stir in cooked sausage.
Form dough into 1 inch balls; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen appetizers.

title: onion crusted chicken
directions: Place chicken between plastic wrap and flatten.
Salt and pepper.
Combine butter, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Stir well.
Dredge chicken in butter mixture, then in crushed onion rings.
Arrange in baking dish.
Top with remaining onion.
Drizzle remaining butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Toast bread; spread with butter.
Cut toasted bread into cubes.
Layer toast cubes, bacon and cheese 1/2 at a time in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add milk, salt and pepper; beat until smooth.
Pour over layers.
Chill overnight. Sprinkle with cornflakes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown and set.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: e z chicken strips
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips.

Mix flour, salt, pepper and the baking powder in a medium size bowl. Combine the milk and egg; beat well. Combine the flour mixture to milk and egg mixture and stir very well. Dip the chicken strips in the batter mixture, coating both sides.
Place in a large skillet with oil or shortening and deep fry until the strips are golden brown in color.
Serve with your favorite sauces.
Makes 8 to 10 strips.

title: standing rib roast
directions: Clean garlic clove; cut in half.
Spear roast with pockets, different depths.
Place 1 piece garlic in each.
Rub roast with oil.
Combine seasonings and rub to coat.
Place on rotisserie; cook 18 minutes per pound.
For medium, 160°; rare, 140° and for well, 170°.

title: mama mitchell's date squares
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients and put half in a greased rectangular pan.
Cook the remaining ingredients in a pan until thick, stirring constantly.
Spread over the oatmeal mixture. Then top with the remaining oatmeal mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes (no more) at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut bread into cubes and place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread bacon over bread.
Mix eggs and milk together, then pour over bacon.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
This dish may be prepared ahead and frozen.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix together the 10x sugar, butter and ice cream topping. Spread on top of cooled brownies.
Melt the chocolate chips and butter on stove.
Pour over brownies in pan and spread smooth. Refrigerate. Cut into squares with warm knife.

title: strawberry margarita
directions: Mix in blender.
Garnish with fresh lemon or lime slices. Crushed ice optional if strawberries aren't frozen.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut bread into 1/2-inch strips.
Arrange layers in buttered baking dish.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and milk.
Stir in raisins.
Mix well and pour over bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: best chocolate pie
directions: Meringue:
Beat egg whites until stiff and add 2 teaspoons sugar.

title: diabetic applesauce cake
directions: Combine all the ingredients and pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: surprise salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add water.
Refrigerate until set.
Add cheese, pecans and Cool Whip.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: chocolate zucchini drops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except walnuts.
Mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 11 minutes or until set.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream eggs, butter and sugar.
Add flour, sour cream, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
In a small bowl, mix nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Grease an angel food cake pan or Bundt pan.
Put 1/3 of batter in pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of topping, then 1/2 of batter, 1/2 of topping and then rest of batter.
Bake 55 minutes at 350° or until done.
Cool in pan.
Turn out onto plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: picante black-eyed peas
directions: Saute pepper and onion in margarine.
Stir into peas and simmer until thick or until you think ingredients have blended their flavors, about 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: seafood enchiladas(great low-fat recipe)
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine taco sauce and sour cream.
Set aside.
In a blender or food processor or bowl, combine cottage cheese, milk, garlic and salt.
Cover and blend or process until mixture is smooth.
Set aside.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of green onion.
Spread 1 tablespoon of taco sauce mixture over each tortilla.
Top each with cheese, seafood and remaining green onion.
Spoon remaining taco sauce mixture into bottom of a greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Roll up tortillas and place seam side down in baking dish.
Pour cottage cheese mixture over tortillas; sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon broiled chicken
directions: Rub chicken on all sides with cut surface of lemons. Cover and refrigerate chicken 3 to 4 hours. Brush with melted butter; sprinkle with salt, pepper, m.s.g. and paprika.

Place skin side down in broiler pan without rack. Broil 5 to 7 inches from heat, about 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Brush occasionally with butter. Turn and broil 15 to 20 minutes longer. About 3 minutes before end of broiling time, sprinkle with sugar.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter and shortening. Slowly add sugar until well creamed and fluffy. Sift flour, measure, sift with baking powder and salt. Add flour and milk. Pour into greased pan. Bake at 325° about 1 hour and 15 minutes. Do not open oven until cake is done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat all ingredients together and place into two loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Cook bacon and add all other ingredients. Mix well and bake 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: coconut joys
directions: Melt butter in microwave in a large bowl.
Add powdered sugar and coconut; mix well.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of the mixture into balls.
Indent center of each and place on cookie sheet. Melt chocolate in microwave.
Fill centers with melted chocolate. Chill until firm.
Store in the refrigerator.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook in salt water for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and cool.

title: scalloped corn and tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place thawed corn into a 2-quart casserole.
In a large skillet, saute onions in 1/4 cup butter until tender and golden. Stir in tomatoes, salt, sugar and pepper until well blended.
Combine with corn.
Top with bread crumbs. Drizzle with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: like baby ruth bars
directions: Combine sugars and syrup in pan and bring to just a boil.
Add peanut butter and peanuts.
Mix until smooth.
Do not boil.
Pour over corn flakes and mix well.
Pat into slightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put Hershey bar(s) on top and put in the oven until melted.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and onions in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes and onions.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: meatball appetizer
directions: Combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice and heat until jelly is dissolved.
Add meatballs and simmer as long as desired. Serve hot.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken; cool and bone.
Lay in bottom of baking dish. Mix sour cream and soup together; spread over top of chicken.
Melt oleo; mix with broken up crackers and poppy seeds.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook like regular pancakes.

title: pie crusts
directions: Add salt and sugar to flour.
Cut in Crisco.
Beat egg and add water and vinegar.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Mix well.
Divide into 5 or 6 balls and and wrap separately.
Freeze or roll out to fit pie tins and freeze.

title: bunch pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in Crisco until looks like wet meal.
Add water and mix well.
Roll out about 18 pie crusts. Put wax paper between each pie plate.
Stack with wax paper, seal in plastic bag and freeze.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together; pour in sprayed square baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, milk, water and salt about 5 minutes or until it starts to form a soft ball.
Add peanuts and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar.
Stir.
Pour into buttered muffin pans, quickly.
Yields 26 to 30 patties.

title: quick garlic sticks
directions: Cut each bun lengthwise into fourths to make 4 sticks.
In a small saucepan, heat butter, Parmesan and garlic powder until butter melts.
Brush butter mixture lightly on cut sides of buns, using a pastry brush.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Place sticks on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes, or until toasted. Serve hot.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter.
Pour melted mixture over Crispix
cereal.
Stir together until cereal is coated.
Pour cereal into a bag.
Pour powdered sugar in bag with cereal.
Shake bag until cereal mixture is coated with sugar. This is a great snack.
Kids
and adults both love
it!

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugars until blended; beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir in milk, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add alternately flour and buttermilk.
Pour into a buttered and floured pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix together sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden.

title: mexican style casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese and corn chips. Bake at 375° for 25 to 40 minutes.
Top with cheese and add on top of corn chips.

title: pound cake delight
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco until creamy; add eggs one at a time and beat well after each one.
Add Pet milk and flavoring; beat well. Add flour, a small amount at a time; mix well and pour into a large tube pan that
has been greased and floured.
Put in cold oven and set for 300°.
Bake for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
This is a delicious cake!

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onions in butter and rice.
Combine consomme and cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Brown rice in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Bake about 2 hours at 350°.
Sprinkle top with crushed corn flakes the last half hour.

title: linda's drop biscuits
directions: Blend flour and Crisco well. Add buttermilk as needed to thin to drop off a spoon.
Grease a medium iron skillet; preheat.
Bake for 9 to 10 minutes on top rack at 500°.

title: saucy short ribs
directions: Prepare ribs in a pressure cooker according to the directions in cooker.
Pour off fat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine barbecue sauce with remaining ingredients and pour over ribs. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Baste well, bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serve with hot rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix brown sugar, white Karo and oleo.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda, salt and butter flavoring.
Pour over the popped corn and mix well.
Spread on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 200°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Place slices of bacon (cut into thirds) on the bottom of an electric skillet.
Put small hamburger patties on the top of the bacon.
Add a thinly sliced onion, sliced carrots, a little celery cut small, sliced potatoes, and top with a green pepper sliced in small pieces. (Any raw vegetables may be added.)

title: tuna chowder
directions: Cook rice and onion in water until done.
Add soup and tuna; mix well.
Season
with salt and pepper to taste.

title: pound cake
directions: Add cake mix to remaining ingredients.
Cook at 350° about 55 minutes in a tube pan.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients. Cut in shortening as for pie crust. Add milk.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Cover meat and bones with water.
When boiling, skim.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, onion, parsley, salt, basil, pepper, garlic powder and bay leaf.
Boil for 1 1/2 hours; add carrots and celery.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Add macaroni, green beans and peas.
Cook another 20 minutes.
Then add kidney beans and heat thoroughly. (Serve with Parmesan cheese and garlic bread.)

title: shocking pink dip
directions: Put cream cheese in bowl; add gelatin and milk to cream cheese.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended and smooth.
Put mixture into serving bowl.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Let dip stand at room temperature to soften slightly.
Serve with a plate of fruit.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: p.a. chicken dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix sour cream and soft cream cheese. Mix until smooth and creamy. Add Parmesan and mix well. Add onion and all seasonings, except paprika. Sprinkle paprika for garnish. Spread in prepared 8 x 8 baking pan. Bake approximately 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are lightly golden brown.

title: calico jello salad
directions: In separate bowls, mix orange, lime and cherry Jell-O with 1 cup hot water and 3/4 cup cold water.
Pour into flat pans so when Jell-O is set it can be cut in cubes.
Prepare lemon or pineapple Jell-O as directed on box.
Let chill until syrupy.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook meat, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Heat through.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: In a jar with lid, combine vinegar with sugar, oil, pepper and pepper sauce.
Cover and shake until well-blended.
Makes about 3/4 c.

title: four layer delight
directions: 1st. Layer:
Melt butter in 9 x 13 Pyrex dish.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix-spread over bottom of dish.
Bake 375° for 15 minutes. Cool completely.
2nd Layer:
Cream 8 oz. cream cheese with 1 cup confectionery sugar (10 x).
Add 1-8 oz. container Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Spread over crust.
3rd Layer:
Mix 2 small instant chocolate pudding mixes with 3 cups milk.
Blend well.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Cool.
4th Layer:
Top with 8 oz. Cool Whip.
Sprinkle Nuts over top.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Beat butter in large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add molasses; beat well. Combine soda and water, stirring until soda dissolves.
Add to creamed mixture.
Combine flour and remaining ingredients; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheets and flatten slightly with a flat bottomed glass dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes or until done.
Cool slightly on cookie sheet; remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: holiday cranberry pineapple desert
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save juice and add water to make 2 cups liquid.
Boil, add to Jello, let cool.
In another bowl, mix cranberry sauce and pineapple together.
Do not use mixer.
When Jello is cool, add to cranberry pineapple mixture and refrigerate.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix sugar and syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
(Mixture will be light brown.)
Add margarine and vanilla; microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Add soda, while stirring gently.
(Mixture will become foamy.)
Pour into buttered cookie sheet. Let cool completely and break into pieces.

title: breakfast eggs
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add milk, mustard and bread.
Stir in cheese and sausage.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate overnight.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: ham-cheese-potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, heat cheese and cream, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted and sauce is creamy.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.

title: breakfast skillet
directions: Combine milk, au gratin sauce packet, hot sauce, eggs and mustard. Stir in dried potatoes, mushrooms and bacon. Cover. Cook on high 2 1/2 to 3 hours or on low 5 to 6 hours. Sprinkle cheese over top. Cover until melted.

title: sausage jubilee
directions: Saut cut up sausage in a pan for 3-5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, water, corn and salsa.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 15-20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Great for a quick hot meal.

title: bananas foster
directions: Mix butter
and
brown	sugar
in
skillet.
Cook
over medium heat until sugar is melted.
Slice bananas in halves or quarters; add
to
butter
mixture, cooking until tender.
Add liqueur
and stir.
Sprinkle rum and brandy over top.
Ignite; spoon
gently a few times.	Serve warm over vanilla ice cream. Serves 6.

title: brown (raisin) bread
directions: Cook raisins in 3 cups water in a pan with a tight lid for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add vegetable shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together dry ingredients and add liquid mixture.
Mix until thoroughly mixed.
Grease and dust with flour, 6 mini loaf pans or 6 cans (like soup cans).
Pour mixture into pans.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Makes 6 small loaves.

title: tarragon or dill vinegar
directions: Poke tarragon or dill sprigs into a bottle.
Fill with vinegar.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add milk, cranberries and melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes in a greased mold or tube pan.
Cut cake into wedges and serve with sauce.
We enjoy this at Thanksgiving and Christmas.

title: red beans and sausage
directions: Crisp fry bacon and reserve.
Saute chopped celery and onions in 3 to 4 tablespoons bacon grease until very soft.
Add parsley and mashed garlic; saute for 5 minutes.
Deglaze pot with broth; add presoaked prepared beans, bay leaves and crumbled bacon.
Use seasonings to taste and bring to a simmer.
Grill or bake sausage to remove grease.
Cut into bite size pieces and add to beans. Simmer for at least 1 hour.
All measurements are approximate (experiment).
Serve over rice.

title: "glorified" pork chops
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot oil brown chops, doing half at a time with onion, about 10 minutes.
Drain fat off.
Stir in soup and water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, until chops are fork-tender, stirring occasionally. Makes 6 servings.

title: garlic cheese spread for bread
