directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Slice a loaf of French or Italian bread into 1-inch slices.
Spread garlic cheese mixture between slices.
Bake on baking sheet for 12 to 15 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: ham dinner rolls
directions: Slice top of dinner rolls.
Put chopped ham and cheese on bottom part.
Replace top half.
Saute onion, mustard, poppy seed and butter and pour over rolls.
Warm in oven until heated through.

title: dijon mustard vinaigrette
directions: Whisk together vinegar and mustard.
Add the oil slowly, whisking until thickened and smooth.

title: ski slope soup
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Combine all other ingredients, except potatoes. Simmer for 1 hour.
Add potatoes and cook until potatoes are done, about 20 minutes. Take out bay leaves and mash.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Measure the crushed cereal into a shallow dish or pan.
Set it aside.
In a small bowl, beat the egg and milk slightly with a fork.
Add the flour, salt and pepper; mix until smooth.
Dip the chicken pieces in the mixture.
Roll the pieces in the crushed cereal.
Place the pieces in a single layer in a greased or foil-lined shallow baking pan.
Drizzle the melted butter over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until the chicken is tender.
Don't cover the pan or turn the chicken while baking.

title: creamy baked cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into well-buttered casserole dish with cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until bubbly and softly set.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add all other ingredients.
Put into casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: walnut apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs slightly. Beat in oil and vanilla.
Stir together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Stir in alternately with apple sugar mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake at 350° in greased, floured angel food pan for about 1 hour, or until toothpick inserted in top comes out clean. Or, bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan about 35 minutes.

title: shredded pork
directions: Remove bone from steak.
Thinly slice steak; set aside.
In small bowl combine soup, water, sherry, soy sauce, ginger and crushed green pepper or red peppers until crisp.
Transfer to bowl. In skillet over high heat in 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry carrots and peppers until crisp.
In same skillet, stir-fry pork half at a time, until pork is no longer pink.
Stir in cooked vegetables and soup mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon icebox cake
directions: Combine cookie crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Press 1 cup of mixture into buttered pan.
Chill.
Save remaining crumbs for top.
Beat egg yolks until thick; add condensed milk.
Add lemon rind, juice and almond extract; stir until thick.
Beat egg whites; add remaining sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold into condensed milk and lemon mixture.
Pour into pan; top with crumbs. Freeze for 4 to 6 hours.

title: holiday appetizer
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Stir in beef, onion, green pepper and pepper; mix well.
Stir in sour cream.
Spoon into 8-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle walnuts over top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with assorted crackers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Layer broccoli, raisins, bacon, pecans and cheese in glass salad bowl.
Mix together mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar and toss with salad.

title: holiday cookie mix
directions: In large bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Store in canister; store at room temperature for up to 6 weeks.
(For longer storage, place in freezer.)
Makes 23 cups.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Put water, oleo, sugar and raisins in saucepan and boil 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
When mixture is cool, add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour a large jelly roll pan with 1-inch sides.
Spread batter in the pan and bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until done.
Glaze with powdered sugar frosting; cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix cream of celery soup and sour cream; spread over chicken.
Crumble crackers and spread over top.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh berry syrup
directions: In a blender or food processor puree the berries with apple juice. Pour into a saucepan and add cornstarch. Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens, about 3 minutes. Add sugar, lemon rind and lemon juice. Pour over pancakes, waffles or french toast.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes; gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
In a separate bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Gradually add pumpkin mixture to the flour mixture.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add tomato sauce; save 1/4 of sauce.
Add taco seasoning and heat.
Mix beans and 1/4 of tomato sauce.
Line baking dish with corn chips; pour meat mixture over chips and spread beans on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover with grated cheese and crumbled corn chips.
Return to oven until cheese melts.
Serve with lettuce, sour cream and tomatoes.
To make without beans, cut recipe in half.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Pour Chex cereals into large bowl; set aside.
In 1-quart microwave-safe bowl combine Hershey's semi-sweet chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereals, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal mixture into large Glad Lock zipper bag with powdered sugar.
Seal securely and shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Mash. Mix mashed potatoes, sour cream, cream cheese, milk, salt and pepper. Place in casserole dish. Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop-bean bake
directions: In ovenproof skillet, brown chops on both sides.
Remove from pan.
Pour off drippings.
Blend in soup and thyme.
Stir in beans.
Arrange chops on top.
Sprinkle on salt and pepper. Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Uncover; cook to desired consistency, 5 to 10 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: granny's sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter until fluffy.
Add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Sift flour and salt together 3 times.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Add soda to sour cream.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream, mixing well with each addition.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan.

title: cranberry cream dream salad
directions: If using frozen cranberries, let thaw before using. In a food processor or blender, grind the cranberries. Add the sugar, crushed pineapple and marshmallows. Let mixture stand overnight. Just before serving, stir in the sliced banana and whipped cream. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: marinated mix vegetables
directions: Fix vegetables.
Take 5 Sweet 'N Low packets and sprinkle over vegetables.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Mix and marinate overnight for best results.

title: pot roast
directions: Mix together flour, salt and pepper and rub on meat.
Melt shortening in large Dutch oven; brown meat and reduce heat.
Add water and Worcestershire.
Cover tightly and simmer about 4 hours or until meat is tender.
About 1 hour before end of cooking time, add vegetables.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: canned string beans
directions: Boil in mixture for 30 minutes.
Place in hot jars and seal.

title: tuna plate
directions: Line 4 plates with lettuce.
Top with tuna.
Surround with vegetables, crackers and lemon.

title: spinach squares
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat eggs.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Add cheese and spinach.
Mix well. Spread into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 40 squares.

title: rolls
directions: Using a large bowl, add ingredients in order.
Add 5 cups of flour, then beat well.
Add 2 more cups of flour, knead remaining flour in by hand until not sticky.
Let rise until doubled.
Make into rolls.
Rise.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: gingersnaps
directions: In saucepan, combine maple syrup, butter and brown sugar.
Boil until melted.
Stir in everything else except the flour.
Remove from heat.
Cool in large bowl until lukewarm.
Gradually stir in flour.
Wrap dough in wax paper and refrigerate between 1 hour and overnight.
Roll out small portions of dough, paper thin on floured cutting board.
Cut desired shapes.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes at 350°. Store in airtight container.
They keep 2 weeks or more!

title: fruit enchiladas
directions: Spoon fruit filling evenly down center of each tortilla; sprinkle evenly with cinnamon. Roll up and place seam side down in lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Bring butter and next three ingredients to a boil in a medium saucepan. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly 3 minutes.
Pour over enchiladas. Let stand 30 minutes. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut beef into chunks and put into roaster (small).
Add soups; do not brown beef.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours, covered.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken and celery with French dressing.
Marinate at least 2 hours in refrigerator.
Add chopped walnuts and mayonnaise to taste; mix well.
Add eggs; mix lightly.
Garnish with chopped olives and capers.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: pecan haystacks
directions: Beat egg white until very stiff.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Mix well.
Add pecans; coat well.
Drop by small spoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake at 200° for 25 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Do not remove cookies until oven is very cool.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple into oblong cake pan, top with cherry pie filling, cover with white cake mix. Take 1 can of chopped walnuts and pour over entire mixture. Put melted butter over everything. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Rub the pork with vegetable oil, then season with the Old Bay and the garlic. Heat grill to medium; grill on either an outdoor or indoor grill.
Grill the pork over the medium heat until the internal temperature reaches 160°, about 30 to 50 minutes. Keep checking so as not to under or overcook, turning often to grill evenly.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and set aside.
Cook bacon in 10-inch skillet until crisp.
Drain bacon, reserving fat in skillet.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Cut warm potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Add potatoes and crumbled bacon to mixture.
Heat until hot and bubbly, stirring gently to coat potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: adventurous beans
directions: Combine all ingredients into large casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Add grits to boiling salted water. When done, add remaining ingredients. If fluffier grits are desired separate eggs and beat egg whites. Put in 3-quart casserole dish; bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 12.

title: tuscana soup(better than olive garden's)
directions: Slice sausage and brown in medium frying pan.
Drain off fat. Add and saute onion and garlic with sausage.
In soup pan (5-quart pan), put chicken broth and water, carrots, sausage, onion, garlic and potatoes.
Cook over medium heat until potatoes are done.
Mash some of the potatoes; add milk.
Add chopped kale.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes; add table cream.
Serve hot with shredded Romano cheese on top.
Serves 4.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, mix all ingredients except 1/2 of onion.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes more.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in
salt
water for 8 minutes.
Drain, but not too dry.
Brown ground beef in margarine in heavy skillet. Season with 1/2
teaspoon
salt
and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add onion and then
soups.
Blend
well and contiune cooking until heated thoroughly.
Add noodles and heat until hot.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with skin on.
Cool, peel, then dice potatoes or cut up.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt 1/2 butter.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour sauce over potatoes; mix lightly. Cover top with remaining butter, sliced over the top.
Cover with cornflake crumbs (1 to 1 1/2 cups).
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix together in saucepan and cook on medium-high heat until thick and clear.
Stir often.

title: easy 3 cheese tuna souffle
directions: In bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, arrange croutons.
In medium bowl, beat together milk, eggs and soup; stir in cheeses and tuna.
In small skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add celery, onion and mushrooms; saute until onion is soft. Spoon sauteed vegetables over croutons; pour egg-tuna mixture over top.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake in 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: six minute chocolate cake
directions: Measure and mix all ingredients except vinegar.
Mix thoroughly.
Quickly stir in vinegar.
Pour batter quickly into square cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Put pears, peppers and onions in food chopper (coarse blade). Drain.
Add other ingredients to vinegar and boil 15 minutes.
Add pears, peppers and onions.
Boil about 30 minutes longer.
Pack in hot jars and seal.
Makes 12 pints.

title: coconut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add coconut, flour and soda.
Mix together.
Form into walnut-sized balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.
Do not overbake.
(Should be very light in color.)

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Combine boiling water and Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 4 cup mold or 8-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil; let cool.
Add large box of Jell-O (orange); mix well until covered.
Add buttermilk.
Let cool; mix well.
Then add Cool Whip and mix well.
Chill.

title: sesame-ginger chicken(nutritious)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Place chicken between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Coat grill rack with vegetable cooking spray; place on grill over medium-hot coals.
Place chicken on rack and cook 4 minutes on each side, basting frequently with soy sauce mixture.
Transfer chicken to serving platter; garnish with green onion, if desired. Yields 4 servings (about 201 calories per serving).

4.4; carbohydrate:

363; calcium:

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars.
Add eggs.
Beat.
Add other ingredients; drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: scotchy peanut bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter; add brown sugar. Cream well. Blend in flour. (Mixture may be crumbly.) Press into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 pan. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Combine sugar and Karo corn syrup in medium saucepan. Bring to a boil; remove from heat. Add butterscotch morsels; stir in, then add peanut butter. Stir to blend. Add Frosted Flakes. Stir to mix. Spread over base. Cool in refrigerator and cut into squares.

title: cheese potatoes in foil
directions: Slice or chop potatoes into a large piece of foil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Crumble bacon over potatoes.
Add onion and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Wrap loosely and seal well with double fold.
Cook in 350° oven for about 1 hour or until done, turning occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.
These are great fixed on the grill!

title: yummy muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix together dry ingredients and raisins.
In blender, combine apple and orange chunks and remaining ingredients. Pour wet mixture into dry ingredients and mix together.
Pour batter into muffin tins lined or sprayed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.
One muffin equals 104 calories (9 calories from fat), 1 g total fat, 0 saturated fat and 0 cholesterol.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on the box.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Tear the angel food cake into bits.
Stir in pudding mixture.
In another bowl, mix cut strawberries in glaze and spread on top of cake mixture.
Refrigerate.
Ready to eat.

title: chili soup
directions: Put butter or lard in frying pan and brown onions; add hamburger and fry until brown.
Add to tomato juice and beans. Add seasonings and simmer 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Makes about 7 quarts.

title: oatmeal gems
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients. Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: surprise pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Arrange sliced candy evenly over cake batter.
Combine water and corn syrup in saucepan; heat just to bubbles appear around edge of pan.
Pour over cake batter and candy.
Bake in preheated 350° oven, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Spoon out of pan while warm.
If desired, serve plain or top with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 8 or 9 servings.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Wash and crisp the spinach. Tear into pieces when crisp. Put water chestnuts over the top.

title: cappelletti in broth
directions: Brown the chicken breast in the butter, seasoning it with salt and pepper; set aside.
Chop mortadella finely and combine in a bowl with chicken, Ricotta, 1 cup (4 ounces./125 g) Parmesan, 1 egg, nutmeg, salt and pepper; mix well.

title: almond-apple crisp(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix water and almond extract.
Toss with apples in a 1 1/2-quart casserole, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix remaining ingredients, except Yogurt Topping, until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake until top is golden brown and apples are tender, about 30 minutes.
Serve warm with Yogurt Topping.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve on a platter with party crackers or sliced raw veggies.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt and then add milk and put on double boiler.
When hot, add 1/2 cup of milk and then add beaten egg yolks.
Stir with wire whisk occasionally over heat for 15 minutes until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and custard 2 times.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: spiced pilaf
directions: Soak the bread crumbs in 1/2 cup of water for 5 minutes. Squeeze dry and place in a bowl.
Add meat, tomato paste, cumin and egg.
Mix together thoroughly.
Season with salt and pepper.
With damp hands, roll the meat into balls about the size of walnuts.

title: old english prime rib
directions: Select choice prime rib or standing rib.
Season meat and rub into meat.
In a large, heavy pan, such as the bottom of a roaster, pour a layer of rock salt until the bottom section of the pan is completely covered.
Lightly dampen the rock salt with water until the salt is just lightly moist.

title: ladyfinger torte
directions: Line spring-form pan on sides and bottom with ladyfingers. Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Whip cream.
Fold into cheese mixture.
Put part of mixture on ladyfingers, then more ladyfingers, then rest of mixture.
Chill 30 minutes before serving.
Spread pie filling on top before serving.

title: stuffing for a pumpkin
directions: Boil potatoes.
Fry onions in margarine.
Place meat in with onions and fry.
Add mashed potatoes.
If too thick, add water. Add spices; stir and keep on low heat for a few minutes.
Place in hollow pumpkin.
Bake at 350° until pumpkin is brown.

title: lime cream cheese pie
directions: In bowl mix cream cheese until smooth, gradually beat in 1/2 cup milk.
Reduce speed.
Add pudding mix, undiluted limeade concentrate and remaining 1 cup milk.
Beat just until blended. Fold in 2 cups whipped topping.
Spoon into pie crust. Refrigerate pie until cream cheese filling is firm enough to slice (at least 3 hours).

title: salad
directions: Fill
a
quart
casserole dish half full of shredded lettuce.
Add in layers
of
celery, onions, green peppers and peas
(thawed,
but
not
cooked).	Add mayonnaise and scatter sugar over it.
Next, add cheese.
Fry bacon and break up over the salad.
Add sliced eggs.
Cover and let stand overnight.

title: pear-pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pear juice.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in pineapple, pears and marshmallows.
Chill until almost firm.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm.

title: calico beans
directions: Saute the hamburger, bacon and onion together. Combine with the remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
If slow cooker is used, mix as directed and low cook for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Slice and cook carrots.
Make white sauce.
Layer carrots and cheese (end with carrots).
Add white sauce and crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pennsylvania dutch potato salad
directions: Blend ingredients in medium saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thick and bubbly.

title: venison pie
directions: Combine salt, pepper and flour in a bag.
Add meat cubes; shake to coat.
In large skillet, melt butter; brown venison and ham over medium heat.
Add water, soup mix, parsley and rosemary. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, adding more water if necessary to keep meat submerged.
Whip together potatoes and eggs.
Spread 4 cups of potato mixture over bottom and sides of oiled 8 x 14 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 5 minutes, then fill with venison mixture and top with remaining potatoes. Bake 30 minutes more.

title: ham fried rice
directions: Beat eggs; slightly scramble in 1 tablespoon oil.
Set aside for later use.
In heavy frying pan over high flame, heat 3 tablespoons oil.
Add scallions; stir a few times.
Add rice; stir quickly until rice is coated with oil.
Mix together the soy sauce and sugar; stir into rice and mix well.
Add ham and eggs, breaking eggs into little pieces.
Serves 4.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together.
Pack mix down firmly and line bottom of baking pan.

title: salmon dip
directions: Mix and roll into a ball.
You can make one larger or two small balls.
Roll into pecans, finely chopped, and/or parsley.

title: rice sambrosa
directions: In ovenproof skillet saute beef, onions and peppers with seasonings until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender. Stir frequently to crumble meat.
Add tomatoes and rice.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: sweet marie bars
directions: In a double boiler, melt peanut butter, brown sugar and corn syrup.
Add butter and vanilla.
Add Rice Krispies and peanuts. Press into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, syrup and salt and bring to boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix well.
Scatter on large shallow pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring frequently.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly	Crisco,
butter, sugar and brown sugar. Add peanut butter and
continue to mix.
Add eggs and mix some more. Add flour 1 cup at a time, mixing thoroughly after each cup.
If dough is
not
stiff
after
2 1/2 cups of flour, add enough flour 1/4 cup
at a time until dough is stiff.
Depending on weather it can
take
up to an extra 3/4 cup of flour. Roll into balls the size of a golf ball.
Place 3 inches apart on a cookie sheet
and flatten with a fork.
Bake until set at 350° about 12 minutes.
Do not
overcook,
they will get very hard if you do.

title: pumpkin dream pie
directions: You may use 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip in place of the Dream Whip, milk and vanilla.

title: fish chowder
directions: Use 6-quart pan.
Cut pork into 1/4-inch cubes.
Brown in pan. Add onion, potatoes and water to cover potatoes.
When potatoes come to a boil, add fish (salt and peppered).
Cook 2 to 3 minutes on low heat.
Turn fish and cook 3 more minutes.
Remove fish and flake.
Add corn, half and half, butter, flaked fish, parsley and thyme.
Simmer slowly and bring almost to boil.
Do not stir too much.

title: sweet potato casserole(6 servings)
directions: In large bowl, combine sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, 1/4 cup butter, vanilla and milk.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar, flour, pecans and remaining butter.
Top sweet potatoes with crumbled mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
If made ahead and chilled, bake 45 minutes.

title: feta cheese salad
directions: Mix and serve.
It's easy, delicious and a crowd pleaser!

title: nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together.
Add milk, egg and nuts.
Let stand in baking pan for 20 minutes.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: carolyn's great scalloped potatoes
directions: Place a layer of the potatoes and onion in a flat baking dish, then sprinkle lightly with flour, salt, pepper and butter pats. Place over this a layer of cubed ham, about 1/2 cup or more. Repeat with a second and third layer.
Pour mixture of soup and milk over potato layers.
Bake at 375° until tender.
Place foil under dish to catch overflow.
A brown crust is very nice to wait for.
A few minutes under the broiler may add this, if you wish. Wonderful with fresh, frozen corn and sour cream on the side.

title: glorified squash
directions: Mash squash and add all ingredients as listed.
Pour in a greased baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: coconut meringue pie
directions: In blender, mix the egg yolks (reserve whites for meringue), flour, salt and 1/2 the milk.

title: polish lasagna
directions: Boil potatoes, mash; add a small amount of milk.
Add Longhorn cheese.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions. Melt oleo in skillet and saute onions until lightly brown.
Heat sauerkraut.

title: hungarian cabbage rolls
directions: Mix egg, beef, onion, rice, salt and bell pepper together and fill cabbage leaves.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with sliced jowl bacon, then spread sauerkraut over this.
Layer cabbage rolls on top of this and spread with tomato soup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 3 hours.

title: lazy nana salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight or at least several hours before serving.

title: burrito pie
directions: Brown beef along with onions and garlic; drain.
Mix in olives, green chilies, tomatoes with chilies, picante sauce, and refried beans.
Stir mixture thoroughly, reduce heat to low, and let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: black-eyed peas and sausage
directions: Let peas soak overnight. Bring peas to a full boil, then pour peas in a colander and rinse. Fill a large stockpot 3/4 full of water. Add peas, ham hock or bones, celery, onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Cook until tender. While peas are cooking, brown the sausage and cook rice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop onion and 2 packages of chopped beef.
Mix in sauce in a bowl.
Form into a ball.
Use last bag of beef for outside of cheese ball.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Mix with soups, sour cream and almonds.
Melt butter and crumble crackers until all butter is taken up.
Top casserole with this and sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Mix the remaining ingredients and add to the broccoli mixture. Chill.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl 5 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve coffee granules in hot water.
Combine with buttermilk.
Combine flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder; add alternately with buttermilk mixture to creamed mixture, beating just until blended.

title: tortilla ham pinwheels
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese and salad dressing mix. Spread over one side of each tortilla. Top with ham and roll up. Refrigerate for 1 hour. Cut into 1-inch slices.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and finely chopped onion; drain.
Cook rice with salt.
Add cooked rice and cream of broccoli soup.
Add milk and shredded cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually until well mixed.
In another bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Then add to butter and sugar, alternating with water.
Add vanilla and then add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Grease tube pan.
Cook for 1 hour and 10 minutes on 300°.

title: custard tart
directions: Combine flour and 1/2 teaspoon of the salt in mixing bowl. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles bread crumbs.
Mix in enough water to form a dough that sticks together.
Shape dough into ball.
Cut in half.

title: corn casserole
directions: Soften cream cheese and oleo.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into buttered casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs (I prefer Town House) and drizzle with 2 tablespoons melted oleo. Bake at 350° until heated thoroughly.

title: prize coconut cake
directions: You may substitute 1 1/2 cups unsifted all-purpose flour instead of cake flour.

title: mom's apple butter
directions: Cook apples with just enough water to keep from sticking. When done, rub through a sieve; add sugar, vinegar and spices. Place in dishpan or large pan on lower rack in oven.
Cook at 325° until thick.
Stir once or twice during cooking.
When done (about 3 hours), place in clean, hot jelly jars and seal.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets. Dip first 2 fingers in cold water and flatten cookies with slight pressure, then take granulated sugar in a teaspoon and tap gently so each cookie has a generous sprinkling of sugar on top. This almost makes a glaze when baked. Cookies are very brittle and crisp and can be kept for several weeks in a tightly covered tin box in the refrigerator. Bake in slightly hotter oven than 350°, but not 375° oven. I set it to 360°. The edges brown too fast in hot oven. Bake 11 minutes, more or less according to oven. Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: shredded wheat biscuits or bread
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling
water
over
2 Shredded Wheat biscuits. Add sugar, salt,
molasses	and shortening.
Let cool. Dissolve yeast cake in 1/2
cup
warm water.
Mix together and add 5 to 6 cups flour or
enough
for	form a firm dough.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Knead
and
set
in
greased bread tins.
Let rise.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks and boil until soft. Boil eggs and cut into pieces. Cut up pickles and onions. In a large mixing bowl, mix potatoes, eggs, pickles, onion, Miracle Whip, sandwich spread, mustard and pickle juice. Adjust amounts of Miracle Whip, sandwich spread and mustard to taste.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs.
Mix and add flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Add apples, nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: yellow cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually, creaming until light.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Beat one minute.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: sauteed asparagus
directions: If using fresh asparagus, wash and trim the bottoms.
Cut fresh or frozen asparagus in 1/2-inch diagonal slices.
Melt shortening in a large skillet.
Saute asparagus over moderate heat about 5 minutes, tossing frequently.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper to asparagus in skillet.
Toss lightly.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: lincoln's glazed onions
directions: Peel onions and cut in half crosswise.
Place cut side up in casserole.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place small chunk of butter on each and top with honey. Cover loosely with foil.
Bake in a 300° to 325° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour, removing foil the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients (batter will be very stiff).
Lightly grease 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake until brown.

title: eggplant sauce or salad
directions: Broil eggplants until tender.
Peel and mash.
Set aside. Chop garlic finely and add to mashed eggplant.
Add vinegar and salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican bean casserole
directions: Brown pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Add beef and drain.
Add rest of ingredients, except for cheese.
Heat well.
Pour in dish and cover with cheese.
Let bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Prepare 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Combine all ingredients.
Blend until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Do not overmix.

title: creole pralines
directions: Mix sugar, salt and milk in saucepan.
Bring slowly to boil to soft ball stage.
Immediately remove from heat and whip until creamy.
Stir in butter, vanilla and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on buttered wax paper and cool.
Makes 18 to 20.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil potatoes in skins.
Cool, peel and grate them.
Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with reserved cheese and paprika.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Allow casserole to reach room temperature before baking (about 1 hour). Bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, mix together cottage cheese, Romano cheese, eggs and bread crumbs.
Set aside.
In frypan (large), brown hamburg and onion until brown.
Add a large jar of spaghetti sauce; add 2 teaspoons garlic salt.
Let simmer while you cook the lasagna spaghetti (12 strips).
Cook for 10 minutes in boiling water; drain when done and let cold water run in pan until its cool enough to handle.

title: cucumber yogurt soup
directions: Put half of the cucumber slices in a food processor with the remaining ingredients and puree.
Transfer the puree to a bowl. Stir in the remaining cucumbers; chill at least 4 hours before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mud pie
directions: Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until tan at 350° (about 20 minutes).
Cool.

title: salsa by kk
directions: Drain salsa of extra juice.
Add chopped tomato and green pepper.
Spread softened cream cheese on round plate or platter. Spread salsa mixture on top of cream cheese.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: rosemary roasted potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Have jelly roll pan ready.
Cut each potato into 8 wedges and set aside.
Peel garlic and cut in 4 slices.
Put garlic in a 1 cup glass measuring cup with oil and cook in microwave on High until hot (45 to 55 seconds).
Remove and discard garlic.
Add pepper and salt to oil.
Crush rosemary between fingers and add to oil.
Stir and add to potatoes and toss.
Transfer potatoes and any loose oil from bowl to pan. Spread potatoes so not touching.
Bake until tender, about 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: burger dinner
directions: Mix ground beef with egg, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and garlic.
Shape into patties and brown on both sides.
Mix mushroom gravy as on package.
Pour over hamburgers.
Simmer for about 1 hour, then serve over noodles.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Heat milk and Carnation milk until hot.
Add sugar mixture and stir well.
Leave on heat 5 to 10 minutes.
Take off and cool.
Add vanilla.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix together well with your hands. Shape into balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until brown.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into flowerets.
Stem mushrooms. Add tomatoes, mix together and add dressing.
Cover and refrigerate.
Let marinate for 7 hours or overnight.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all together, stirring well.
Chill and serve. This is the recipe used on salad bar at Western Sizzlin' East.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Heat together butter, sugar and cocoa.
Mix in a bowl, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Combine and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve desired color and flavor Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add sugar, pineapple juice, 12 cups water, lemon juice and flavoring (to taste).
Place in container(s) and freeze to slushie state.
When serving, add equal parts of punch, ginger ale and Sprite.

title: refrigerator biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix the other ingredients and add to the yeast mixture.
Knead on a floured board until smooth.

title: glorified rice
directions: Cook rice until soft, not mushy.
Mix all ingredients except whipped cream and let stand for one hour.
Put in whipped cream before serving.
Garnish with cherries.
Beat whipped cream before folding in above ingredients.

title: chile-cheese refried bean dip
directions: Cut cream cheese into cubes and soften. Mix together refried beans and cream cheese. Stir in scallions and chiles. Place in slow cooker, cook two hours; add half a cup of shredded cheese and olives. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: quiche
directions: Fry bacon and sausage separately.
Crumble and pour into iron skillet.
Mix eggs.
Add potatoes O'Brien; mix and pour into skillet with bacon and sausage, then mix again.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Pour off grease as needed.
Slice and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into ball. Using waxed paper, roll ball on chopped pecans. Chill for 1 hour; serve with crackers.

title: corn muffins
directions: Sift corn meal, flour, salt, baking powder and sugar together. Beat egg.
Add milk and butter.
Add to sifted dry ingredients, stirring just enough to dampen all the dry ingredients.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in a 425° oven for 25 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 muffins.

title: apple rice crisp
directions: Combine apples, rice, lemon juice, 1/4 cup brown sugar, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Spoon into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix flour and remaining brown sugar, cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in nuts and sprinkle over apple/rice mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender. Serve warm, plain or topped with ice cream.

title: fluffy pineapple pie
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese, pineapple and Cool Whip together. Pour into pie crust.
Can be served right away but is better if it is refrigerated overnight.

title: garden dip
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the yogurt, mayonnaise, red and yellow peppers, celery, shallots and tarragon.
Transfer the dip to a serving bowl.
If desired, cover and chill in refrigerator until serving time.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening together.
Gradually add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add flavorings.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to cream mixture alternately with milk.
Begin with flour and end with flour.
Spoon mixture into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Cut rhubarb into 1/2 inch pieces.
Sift 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour together and mix with rhubarb. Pour into 8 or 9-inch baking pan and dot with butter.
Sift together the remaining cup of sugar and flour with salt and baking powder and stir in beaten egg.
The mixture will be crumbly.
Sprinkle over the rhubarb and shake the pan a little so the crumbs will settle down in rhubarb.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350° or until crust is a delicate brown.
Serve warm or cold with or without cream or ice cream.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Mix Pet milk, marshmallows and orange juice and let stand. Combine graham cracker crumbs, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, raisins, pineapple and cherries. Add this to the marshmallow mixture. Press down in a square Pyrex pan/dish and let stand in icebox. Cover with cloth.

title: ranch house beans
directions: Brown ground chuck. Drain and add all other ingredients. Bake in 2 quart baking dish at 375 degrees for 45 minutes. Do not place lid over beans.

title: fish fry coleslaw
directions: Mix and chill.
Eat all you want, it's lo-cal and fat free!

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix crust ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes; cool.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given adding a dash of salt if you prefer.
Put in greased loaf pan (1 large or 2 small).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: baked pecans
directions: Beat egg white until forms peaks. Mix flour with sugar.
Fold all ingredients into egg white.
Pour over pecans and stir until the pecans are completely coated.
Bake on large cookie sheet lined with brown paper that has been greased on both sides.
Bake 30 minutes at 250°.
Lift up immediately from the brown paper with a spatula.
Cool completely and store in tight container.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine thawed vegetables, soup, sour cream, 1/2 cup each of the cheeses, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer. Ready to serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, bring to a rolling boil on medium heat the sugar, milk and oleo. Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Beat until smooth. Pour into 13 x 10 pan and let cool.

title: graham cracker brownies
directions: Stir ingredients
in a bowl.
Butter and flour a 9 x 9-inch or an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Pour 1 cup warm water in large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt and 1/2 the flour.
Beat with electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Beat in egg and soft shortening.
Mix rest of flour until soft dough to handle.

title: chocolate frosting(microwave)
directions: Put into a microwave dish the first 3 ingredients.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Beat.
Add the vanilla and gradually stir in the confectioners sugar.
Use wire whisk if hand mixing.
If more milk is needed, add 1 teaspoon at a time.
This will cover a two layer cake.

title: buffet mashed potatoes
directions: After potatoes are mashed, add cream cheese and dip.
Put into casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Put into oven and heat thoroughly, gently brown on top.
Can be made day before and reheated in microwave.

title: original toll house chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract until creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes until edges are golden brown.
Let stand on cookie sheets 2 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheets; cool.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: zucchini-carrot casserole
directions: In
medium saucepan, boil zucchini and green onion in a cup of
water
for
minutes; drain.
Stir in the undiluted chicken soup,
sour cream and carrots.
Toss dry stuffing mix with
melted butter and spread half of the stuffing mix in the bottom
of
a 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mix on top.
Sprinkle the rest of the stuffing mix over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Heat sweet potatoes, then mix like mashed potatoes. Combine all the ingredients and beat together with mixer. Then put in buttered pan.

title: inside outside ravioli
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients in a large skillet. Cook spinach or broccoli and drain, reserving liquid. Add water to make 1 cup. Add spinach or broccoli liquid, salt, pepper, chopped spinach or broccoli, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and tomato paste to meat mixture. Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine spinach or broccoli with macaroni and remaining ingredients. Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with meat sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: overnight fiesta salad
directions: Layer the first eight ingredients in a large salad bowl. Refrigerate.
Top with Tostitos and toss.
Serve immediately.

title: chili pie casserole
directions: Place 1 1/2 cups chips in baking dish.
Arrange chopped onion and 1/2 cup cheese over chips.
Pour chili over mixture.
Top with remaining chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. (Serves 6.)

title: western supper
directions: Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate several hours so flavors can blend.
Serve on crisp lettuce. Makes 6 servings.

title: stamp potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and boil the potatoes.
Mash them.
Wash lettuce. Clean and add to the mashed potatoes.
Mix in bacon bits.
Serve warm.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Place cottage cheese in strainer and rinse with water.
Drain well.
Put cottage cheese in blender along with lemon juice and blend until smooth. Add the yogurt at this time.
Blend another 1 to 2 minutes.
Texture will be creamy.
Chill well.

title: monica's heart healthy pie
directions: *To cut down on sugar for diabetics, use 4 cartons of yogurt and leave out sweetened condensed milk.

title: chicken feed
directions: Heat electric skillet to 250°. Melt the oleo and Worcestershire sauce. Add salt. Mix cereal and nuts together; add. Stir until all the cereal is well coated. Cook at 250° for about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In a bowl, stir peanut butter and butter together. Add sugar and stir until combined. Shape into balls and place on wax paper; let dry. Melt chocolate. Dip balls into melted chocolate and place on wax paper. Let dry.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all together; put in baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
This makes a lot.
You can make 2 and freeze one or half the recipe.

title: english muffins
directions: Mix milk, salt, sugar and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water; add beaten egg.
Blend with lukewarm mixture.
Add flour and knead until smooth on a floured board. Let rise in bowl until doubled.
Knead.
Rest 1 minute.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into muffins.
Place on a cookie sheet covered with 1/4 cup cornmeal; top with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Cook on medium hot ungreased griddle for 8 to 12 minutes on each side.
Cool on rack.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, put in sugar, cocoa, milk and butter. Bring it to a boil and let boil for 1 minute.
Take off the stove and add oatmeal and coconut.
Mix up well.
Spoon out onto wax paper.
Let set until firm.

title: crunchy cinnamon chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use kitchen scissors and cut tortillas in half (2 at a time, if you prefer) and then cut each half into 3 wedges.
Place wedges on baking sheet sprayed with butter-flavor nonstick cooking spray.
In small bowl, mix together the cinnamon, sugar and Molly McButter.
Generously sprinkle wedges with sugar mixture.
Spray wedges very lightly with nonstick cooking spray. Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 13 minutes.
These burn easily, so watch carefully.
Entire recipe makes 4 servings.

title: ambush beans
directions: Soak beans overnight or bring to a boil and soak, covered, for an hour. Use just enough water to cover beans by about an inch. Cut salt pork into 1/4-inch slabs and place in cold skillet with the 3 tablespoons lard and slowly fry until golden brown and fat is rendered from the salt pork. Remove salt pork from the pan and set aside to cool. Brown the onions and garlic in the rendered fat until very slightly browned. Add jalapenos to beans. Add the chili powder to the beans. Cut the meat from the rendered salt pork into small squares and add to beans. Add rendered fat and onion to beans and simmer until tender, 2 to 3 hours. Add enough water while cooking to keep beans covered. When beans are done, you can mash a small amount through a sieve to thicken the mixture to your desired consistency.

title: peanut chili
directions: In large pot of water, boil peanuts in salted water until tender. Pour out water. Shell peanuts. Brown meat and dry ingredients in skillet. Add to large pot over medium heat. Add peanuts and additional ingredients; simmer 1 1/2 hours on medium.

title: weight watchers vegetable soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a Dutch oven or crock-pot.
Simmer until vegetables are done or cook all day on low in crock-pot.

title: strawberry shortcuts
directions: Cut pound cake lengthwise into 2 layers, and arrange side by side in an 8-inch square pan (cut sides up).

title: swiss beans
directions: Melt butter, stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar, and onion. Add sour cream.
Cook until thickened.
Fold in beans and heat thoroughly.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Grate Swiss cheese and sprinkle over beans (to your taste).
Combine crumbs with melted butter, sprinkle over cheese.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: madeleines(from france)
directions: Weigh 3 eggs.
Separate and put the whites aside in the refrigerator.
Measure the same weight of flour, sugar and butter. Beat the eggs; gradually add the sugar and add the melted butter, then gradually add the flour.
Add 1 teaspoon of baking powder. Add vanilla flavoring for flavor.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat the egg whites very firm.
(Add a pinch of salt to make the whites firm.)
Mix the whites with the prepared mixture.
Bake for 60 minutes at 300°.
The thermostat can be increased to 350° to 400° for the last 10 minutes to brown the cake.
Cool before removing from the pan.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Very good with cornbread.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and salt; alternate with sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan that has been rubbed with Crisco and dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost with your favorite frosting.

title: brandy slush
directions: Mix all ingredients well and freeze.
To serve, place desired amount in glass and add 7-Up or Squirt.
Keeps a long time in freezer.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix and cook 25 minutes at 350°.
Lightly brown 5 slices of bread.
Melt 1 stick of margarine.
Cube bread and mix with margarine.
Put on top of cooked pineapple and cook 15 minutes. Turn off oven and leave in oven for 15 minutes.

title: deer tenderloin
directions: Cut tenderloin into strips.
Sprinkle with soy sauce and lemon pepper.
Roll tenderloin into a roll and wrap with one strip of bacon.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until tender.

title: chili sauce
directions: Scald and peel tomatoes.
Grind onions and peppers.
Place in a large kettle (stainless steel).
Add tomatoes and cook down until sauce thickens and shrinks.
This could take 2 days.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and place in refrigerator to congeal.

title: baked bean medley
directions: Cook ground beef and onions until brown.
Drain fat.
In colander, drain one can pork and beans, kidney, red and lima beans.
In a large oven pot, add all beans, bacon, sauce, brown sugar, etc.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 24.

title: baked beans for a crowd
directions: In a large skillet fry the bacon over medium heat until the fat is rendered.
Remove the bacon to a dish, leaving about 3 tablespoons fat in skillet.
Fry the onions in the bacon fat until light brown.
Return the bacon to the skillet with the onions.
Add diced peppers, catsup, pepper, brown sugar and butter.
Stir until butter is melted.
Cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Pour the canned beans into a large shallow baking dish.
Cover with the sauce and mix well.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 2 1/4 hours.
May be reheated at 300°.
The sauce alone may be frozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, reserving some cheese for topping.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add the rest of the ingredients to form dough.
Chill dough 2 hours.
Roll dough in walnut-size balls.
Roll dough in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° until light brown but still soft for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 36 cookies.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil and simmer until all vegetables are tender.

title: berry pudding
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in berries.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: surprise meat loaf
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and set aside while preparing the rest.
After blanching the broccoli, wrap the broccoli with the boiled ham and the cheese.
Form the meat mixture around the broccoli, cheese and ham.
Top with the uncooked bacon. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Allow to set for a few minutes. Remove from pan and slice. This will freeze well as individual slices wrapped in foil.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt Nestle Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels over hot (not boiling) water; remove from heat.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add water; beat until smooth.

title: potato rolls
directions: Cool to lukewarm the potatoes, shortening and potato water. Then dissolve yeast into potato mixture.
Add sugar, egg, 1 cup flour and salt.
Mix thoroughly and set in a warm place to rise for 30 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken breasts on wax paper.
Lay slice of ham and cheese in centers.
Roll up and fix closed with toothpicks.
Beat egg and add a bit of milk.
Dip chicken breasts in mixture and then roll in bread crumbs.
Lay on baking pan and pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mother's pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter until creamy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and add gradually.
Add flavorings.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch (25-cm) tube pan at 275° (135°C) for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: shrimp
directions: In a pan, you put a few spoons of oil, the onions, garlic and bay leaf.
You let it fry a little while until the onions turn goldish, then you add the tomato, wine, pepper and red pepper. You let it cook for a few minutes, then you add the shrimp.
Let it come to a boil for about 2 minutes.
You then take the shells off the shrimp.

title: thailand corn fritters
directions: Drain the corn.
Crush the kernels for a few seconds in a blender.
Peel and chop the garlic and onion.
Mix with everything, except the oil.
Heat the oil and drop in a few teaspoonfuls of the mixture.
Fry gently for 3 minutes.
Turn over and repeat.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve them while they're hot.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Mix with crushed pineapple and cook until clear and thick.
Beat egg yolks and add to pineapple mixture.
Cook for 1 minute.
Remove from stove and cool.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Add whipped cream topping.
Simple and delicious.
Trust me.

title: chewy oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins and oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes. Cool and store tightly covered.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Good on shrimp and crabmeat.

title: angie's favorite snack
directions: Melt oleo in iron skillet.
Put a slice of cheese in a flour tortilla and fold in half.
Heat in skillet until cheese has melted.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand.
Then pour in blueberry pie filling and nuts.
Pour into 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Then top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Arrange chicken in square dish with meatier portions toward the edge of the dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; stir well. Pour over chicken.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook at High 14 to 16 minutes.
Let stand covered for 5 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift the first four ingredients.
Add nuts, unbeaten eggs, bananas and melted fat.
Stir quickly and lightly.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake about one hour in a 350° oven. Cool before slicing.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat above ingredients well and pour into a greased casserole dish. Mix topping ingredients and spread over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes.

title: brian's mud cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and cocoa.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat. Stir in flour and peanut butter and mix well.
Gently stir in coconut and walnuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove and spread marshmallow cream (2 jars) while hot.
Let cool and frost.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cream together the first four ingredients until well mixed. Mash potatoes and blend together with creamed mixture until fluffy. Spoon into a well-greased, 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot on top of casserole 2 tablespoons margarine.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese and paprika.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook celery and onion until tender.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch or 10 x 12-inch casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
May need more than 1 pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except water; stir in water slowly.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into 2 greased and floured layer pans or one 9x13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes for layers and 35-40 for long pan; or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes before removing to rack to cool.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in small amount of oil.
Add garlic powder, mushroom soup and chicken broth and cook until heated.
Also add mushrooms and olives.
Line sides and bottom of baking dish with flour tortillas.
Add cooked chicken, then pour soup mixture over chicken.
Spoon Ro-Tel tomatoes over top and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until center of casserole is bubbly and cheese is melted.
This is also good with 2 pounds lean hamburger instead of chicken.

title: grandma's sugar peas
directions: Make a roux with butter; add flour until thickened.
Add juice of peas to roux.
Bring to a boil, then add sweet peas, sugar, salt and pepper.
Boil again and simmer until tender.
(To help thicken, squash about 2 tablespoons peas on side of pot and stir.)

title: crab meat appetizer
directions: Cream the cream cheese with the salt and some of the lemon juice.
Add the crab meat.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: italian tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes and pepper in small wedges.
Slice onions into rings.
Alternate tomatoes, onions and pepper in layers in medium bowl.
Shake dressing well and pour over layers.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add pineapple and mix. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust and chill for several hours.

title: stewed cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until nice and crisp.
Drain the bacon on paper towel.
In the grease that's left in pan, saute the onion and celery.
Then add the chicken broth, tomatoes and sauce.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Then add the crumbled bacon, chopped cabbage and some black pepper.
Simmer until cabbage is tender.

title: special k delight
directions: Place sugar and syrup in large pan, bring to a boil and remove from heat immediately.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Stir in cereal and mix until well coated.
Place this mixture in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over the top.
Let cool and then cut and enjoy.

title: international coffee coolers
directions: Combine milk and coffee in blender.
Blend until dissolved. Add ice cream and blend until smooth.
Garnish as desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add salad oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and slowly add flour mixture to egg combination.

title: microwave sauerkraut meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Microwave 20 minutes, turning halfway through cooking.
Green beans can be added.

title: mississippi green bean casserole
directions: Layer green beans and corn in casserole dish.
Heat soup, sour cream, 1/2 of cheese, water chestnuts, margarine and 1/2 of the onion rings.
Pour over green beans and corn.
Bake 30 minutes, covered, at 350°.
Remove cover. Add remaining cheese, onion rings and all slivered almonds.
Bake, uncovered, 15 more minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, water and mustard seed in saucepan and bring to a boil. Let cool and then pour over cabbage mixture. Allow to stay in refrigerator overnight, covered.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters, reserving 3/4 cup liquor.
Combine crumbs, butter and salt.
Spread half of crumbs in greased casserole large enough to hold oysters in a single layer or divide into 2 casseroles.
Cover with the oysters.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Cover with the rest of the crumbs.
Combine
cream, oyster liquor and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over the oysters.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: bagels
directions: Sift 3 1/2 cups flour with salt.
Soften yeast in half the water, stir into flour.
Beat egg whites lightly.
Add sugar, eggs and oil to remaining lukewarm water.
Blend with flour mixture. Beat to make dough, adding more flour if needed.
Add raisins and cinnamon.
Knead until smooth.
Place in oiled bowl.
Cover with damp cloth.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch down until air is out.
Pull off pieces of dough and roll into ropes.
Moisten ends and squeeze slightly to seal.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Slide a few at a time into boiling water.
Turn after one minute. Cook one minute on other side.
Remove.
Mix egg yolk with 1 teaspoon cold water.
Brush on top of bagels.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° to 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice the potatoes in half horizontally and carefully scoop out the flesh into a bowl, reserving the shells intact.
Combine the potato flesh with the remaining ingredients. Stir until smooth and divide among the 4 shells, piling high.
Bake the potato halves for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly golden on top.
Serves 4.

title: ice cream and cookies
directions: Soften	ice
cream; mix with Cool Whip, nuts and 2/3 of cookies.
Spread
in large shallow pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze.

title: lorie's chocolate special birthday cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt, twice.
Mix buttermilk, cocoa and water into paste in cup.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat after each.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Add vanilla and chocolate paste; beat well.
Pour into two well greased and floured pans (or place wax paper in bottom of pans and grease and flour sides of pans).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Test with toothpick.	Ice cake with Chocolate Peanut Butter Icing.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot grease and brown.

title: pork chops and dressing
directions: Salt and pepper and brown pork chops, then put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine.
Add 1/4 cup of water.
Pour over bread, onion and poultry seasoning.
Put bread dressing on top of chops. Mix 1 can of cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 soup can of water. Pour over chops and dressing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil.

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Beat together and pour into pie shell. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown meat, onions and peppers.
Set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Put 1/2 of corn meal mixture into well greased iron skillet.
Then pour meat mixture on top.
Pour remaining corn meal mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Bake in uncooked pie shell at 350° until brown.

title: shrimp and rice curry
directions: Cook 1 cup rice as directed.
Lightly toss in French dressing. Let cool to room temperature.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients, adding zucchini last.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into small pieces.
Makes about 4 dozen.
Serve warm or cold.

title: rapidrise pizza crust(makes 1 (14-inch) thick pizza)
directions: In large bowl combine 3 cups flour, undissolved yeast and salt.
Stir very warm water and olive oil into dry ingredients. Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 4 to 6 minutes.
Cover and rest on floured surface for 10 minutes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries; reserving 1 cup liquid.
In a large saucepan, combine 3/4 cup of the sugar and the cornstarch.
Stir in reserved cherry liquid.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir for 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining sugar, butter and almond extract; stir in cherries.
Cool slightly.
Transfer filling to a pastry lined 9-inch pie pan.
Top with lattice crust.
Cover edge with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Crust should be golden. Makes 6 servings.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressings and cheese; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Makes 4 servings.
Prep time: 15 minutes plus chilling.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Fry bacon, onion and garlic (if used).
Add vinegar, mustard and brown sugar; boil for 3 or 4 minutes.
(If garlic powder is used, add before boiling.)
Mix with drained beans.
Place in a 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: light pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions. Drain and allow to cool. Add onion, green pepper, tomatoes, salad dressing, salt and pepper to taste. Toss to coat well. Refrigerate. Serves 4.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 cup juice from the fruit.
Let stand to room temperature.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Stir in sherbet until dissolved.
Chill until set.

title: yummy caramel corn
directions: Mix the Karo syrup, brown sugar, salt and butter.
Melt for 2 minutes in microwave; stir.
Add the baking soda.
Pour into bag of popcorn.
Put bag in microwave for 4 minutes.
Take bag out every 45 seconds.

title: torch cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini-artichoke squares
directions: Drain artichokes, reserving marinade; chop.
In large bowl, beat eggs, seasonings and parsley.
Mix in cheese and bread crumbs.
Mince onions and garlic.
Saute in 2 tablespoons of reserved marinade.
Add zucchini and cook 1 minute.
Stir onions, garlic, zucchini and artichoke hearts into cheese mixture. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until firm.
Cool a few minutes and then cut into squares.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cut up 1 cup berries.
Add water, cook and strain.
Add enough more water to make 1 cup .
Add sugar, cornstarch and salt to juice and cook until thick, then cool.

title: quiche
directions: Slice bacon thinly.
Pre-fry bacon and onion over medium heat. Layer bacon and onion in uncooked pie shell. Add grated cheese. Mix egg, milk, flour and seasonings (salt, pepper, Accent).
Pour over cheese. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dot's corn chowder
directions: Place diced celery, onion and carrots in 2 cups water and cook until tender.
Add corn and Pet milk.
Simmer 20 minutes to thicken.
Mix cornstarch and small amount of water until smooth. Add to corn soup and stir well until thickened slightly.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Mix all together except nuts.
Spread in a 8 inch pie plate. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with triscuits or other crackers.

title: mexican panned corn
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper.
Cook onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Add corn, green pepper, olives and salt. Heat, stirring constantly.
Crumble bacon over corn.

title: peanut haystacks
directions: Melt the peanut butter and morsels over low heat.
Add peanuts and noodles.
Make clusters by dropping spoonfuls on wax paper. Cool.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix and bake in 3 layers at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: untossed salad
directions: Layer, do not mix, these ingredients.
Spread over the top 2 cups mayonnaise with 3 teaspoons sugar.
Top with a small jar Romano cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, garnish with crumbled bacon, 2 hard-boiled eggs, chopped, and 1 chopped tomato.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain, stir in butter, parmesan cheese and 2 beaten eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into nest in buttered pan (or 10-inch) pie plate.
In skillet cook and drain meat, add sauce, Italian seasoning.
Mix in a large bowl, add ricotta cheese, mozzarella cheese and 1 beaten egg.
Spread cheese mixture over spaghetti nest in the center.
Cover with sauce mixture and cover with tin foil.
Bake at 350 degree for 1 hour.
Cover with mozzarella cheese and bake uncovered for 5 minutes more.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, dissolve the bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add rice.
Lay chicken parts on top of rice.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over this.
Spoon undiluted cream of mushroom soup over top. Cover and bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients all together and bake in casserole dish for 3 hours at 350°.

title: layer salad
directions: Cook and chill peas.
Cook bacon crisp and break into small pieces. Arrange in layers as listed.
Let set for at least 8 hours.
Stir well and serve.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 eggs and cake mix, then mash down onto
oleo.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese
and
powdered
sugar until smooth.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 325°
to 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain off grease.
Spray baking pan with Pam. Line bottom of small baking pan with half of crescent rolls. Spread sausage over rolls; spread cheese over sausage.
Use remaining crescent rolls and spread over cheese.
Bake according to crescent rolls directions or until golden brown.
To make in regular cake pan, double the recipe.

title: penny carrots
directions: Combine soup, sugar, vinegar, oil and mustard.
Mix and add onion and pepper.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Put drained carrots in bowl and pour mixture over them.
Marinate in refrigerator. Serve either warm or cold.
Carrots should be sliced into thick slices before cooking.
Keeps in refrigerator 2 weeks.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, peanut butter and melted margarine in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed 1 to 2 minutes.
Press 1/2 of cake mixture into bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a large bowl, mix Marshmallow Fluff and peanut butter. Cook sugar, salt and milk to soft boil stage.
Pour cooked mix in the peanut butter mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool to harden and cut into squares.

title: catfish courtbouillon
directions: Season fish with salt, pepper, and garlic; put in covered dish and chill several hours.

title: italian corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Toss and brown sausage, drain off most of grease.
Boil with soup and rice, add water and cook 7 minutes.
Mix in pepper, onion and almonds.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in covered casserole dish.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Brown beef and drain excess fat.
Add salt, pepper and onion powder to meat and spread in pie pan.
In separate bowl, mix Bisquick, milk and eggs with hand beater until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake 25 minutes and top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Cool for 5 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts, dredge in flour and salt.
Panfry 10 minutes or until done.
Mix pineapple juice, honey, teriyaki sauce and chives together.
Pour over chicken, add pineapple and heat thoroughly.
Serve with rice.

title: cheddar chicken
directions: Mix soups and sour cream.
Put half of the cream mixture on the bottom of baking pan.
Place chicken breasts in cream mixture. Cover with remaining cream.
Sprinkle with paprika, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
The kids love this.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased pan.
Grease pan well. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook together frozen vegetables, onions and celery in boiling salted water.
Add undiluted cream of mushroom soup, water chestnuts (cut up), mushrooms and a tiny bit of garlic powder in soup.
Mix.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Top with corn flake crumbs and sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° until bubbling.

title: play dough
directions: Mix well.
Cook at medium heat until it's all in one ball. Store in tight container.

title: beef zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion and beef together in skillet.
Arrange beef, zucchini (sliced), then cheese in layers.
Add another layer. Pour soup over top and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nachos
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Using the largest holes on the grater, carefully grate the cheese over wax paper.
You should have about 3/4 cup.
Place the chips flat on a cookie sheet. Using a measuring spoon, spread 1/2 teaspoon salsa on each chip, then sprinkle the cheese evenly on each chip.
Cook until cheese is bubbly.
Let nachos cool for 2 minutes, then serve.

title: grandma's prune cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add to shortening, milk, vanilla and egg.
Batter will be thick.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay prunes which have been washed on top of batter and sprinkle with sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: friendship tea(russian tea)
directions: Keep mixture in airtight jar.
To serve, add 2 to 3 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: daddy's pecan pie
directions: Boil syrup and sugar together for 2 to 3 minutes.
Beat eggs and pour slowly into syrup.
Add butter, salt and vanilla, stirring to blend.
Add pecan pieces.
Pour into raw pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (until set).

title: dirt pudding
directions: Place 2/3 crushed cookies in bottom of 10 x 15-inch pan.
Whip the cream cheese and margarine.
Add whipped topping.
Add milk. Add pudding.
Whip until mixture becomes thick.
Put mixture on top of crushed cookies.
Complete with remaining cookies on top of mixture.

title: rachel's beans
directions: Brown beef on high; pour off grease.
Add cheese to beef to melt.
Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Put in baking dish. Slice onion on top.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 325°.

title: baked limas and sausage
directions: Pick over beans, cover with cold water.
In the morning, drain, cover with cold water and simmer until tender.
Put beans in casserole, add cut up green pepper, sugar, salt and sausage.
Heat the tomato soup with juice and pour over the beans.
If the dish looks a little dryish, add more tomato juice.
Cover and bake at 275° about 5 to 6 hours.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Allow butter, eggs and sour cream to come to room temperature. Add soda to sour cream then add to butter and sugar which has been creamed together and beat 2 minutes.
Add 2 eggs at a time, alternating with flour until all is used.
Add flavorings.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 275° oven.

title: barbecue pork sauce
directions: Bring all this to a boil.
Cool.
Put over meat or store in jars.
Use on chopped hog meat.

title: marie's corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water.
Add cheese, corned beef, onion, soup, salt and pepper.
Cover with seasoned bread crumbs and a little butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Use half to line bowl. Save the other half for topping.
Mix the Cool Whip and milk.
Add orange juice and oranges.
Pour in lined bowl. Sprinkle topping over mixture. Refrigerate.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Toss fruit and almonds together and stir in mayonnaise. Chill.
May serve on lettuce.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers in blender.
Mix together butter, orange juice, coconut, pecans and wafers until well mixed.
Sift powdered sugar.
Roll small balls of mixture in sugar.

title: spiced candied nuts
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar and ground cinnamon.
Stir in evaporated milk and water.
Cook to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and whole nuts.
Stir until you can't stir any more.
Turn out onto wax paper and separate.
Keep in airtight container.

title: quick chicken gravy
directions: Blend together the flour and milk, add to soup and season with pepper.
Heat slowly to boil and cook until thick.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Melt butterscotch bits and margarine.
Add cracker crumbs and nuts.
Press half of this mixture into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and egg.
Pour over prepared pan.
Top with rest of crumbs.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° (325° if using glass dish) or until toothpick comes out clean.
