Cool to room temperature or freeze before cutting into bars.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 11 x 14-inch baking dish.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Cover top with Italian bread crumbs or crushed
potato
chips.
Bake
at
350° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put drained fruit cocktail and mandarin orange in a large bowl.
Sprinkle dry pudding over it.
Pour pineapple juice and all over.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: "top your own" pizza bar
directions: Lightly grease 4 cookie sheets or pizza pans.
Sprinkle lightly with yellow cornmeal if desired.
Open refrigerated dough, unroll contents of each 10 oz. can onto a cookie sheet.
Cut into quarters; press each into 6 inch circle or square, pinching a rim of dough around the edge to form a crust.
Top as desired.
Bake in preheated 425° oven 10 to 14 minutes or until cheese is melted and crust is lightly browned.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Whip cream until stiff.
Add cream cheese, softened.
Mix until smooth.
Grate onion and mix.
Add shrimp and 1/4 of shrimp juice.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with chips or whatever.

title: blueberry fruit crunch
directions: Sift out blueberries and soak in cold water.
Drain.
Place fruit filling in an 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon and extract evenly over filling.
Sprinkle blueberries over this.
Toss with a fork until crumbly:
dry muffin mix, melted butter and nuts. Sprinkle over top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar together.
Add raisins.
Beat eggs and add to buttermilk.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Do not overmix!
Bake in a greased 9-inch round pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add cereal. Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or wax paper, press mixture evenly into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: chewy squares
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Spread in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken marbella
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken quarters, garlic, oregano, pepper and coarse salt to taste, vinegar, olive oil, prunes, olives, capers and juice and bay leaves.
Cover and let marinate, refrigerated, overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken in a single layer in one or two large, shallow baking pans and spoon marinade over it evenly.
Sprinkle chicken pieces with brown sugar and pour white wine around them.
Bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour, basting frequently with pan juices.
Chicken is done when thigh pieces, pricked with a fork at their thickest, yield clear yellow (rather than pink) juice.
With a slotted spoon, transfer chicken, prunes, olives and capers to a serving platter.
Moisten with a few spoonfuls of pan juices and sprinkle generously with parsley or cilantro.
Pass remaining pan juices in a sauceboat.

title: mushroom-broccoli dip
directions: In a large saucepan, saute butter and onions.
Stir in cream of mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Add 1/2 cup milk.
Melt Velveeta cheese in mixture.
Cook broccoli in separate pan and drain.
Add to mixture.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In a 9 x 14-inch glass cake dish layer the fresh vegetables and the bacon pieces.
Mix the salad dressing and the sour cream together with salt and pepper.
This would be layer 6. Layer 7 - grated cheese.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and green pepper in skillet; drain fat off.
In pot, put the tomatoes (smashed up), 1/2 can tomato juice and 1/2 can water.
Let ingredients come to a boil.
Add hamburger, onions and green pepper; turn down to medium low.
Add kidney beans and 1/2 small can chili powder.
Let simmer for 1 hour.
Keep stirring.
You can use more beans, if desired.

title: freckle-face taters
directions: Quarter hot potatoes lengthwise and place in a baking dish. Sprinkle grated cheese over potatoes.
Melt butter in skillet. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir ingredients until bread crumbs are moist.
Crumble mixture over potatoes and broil until cheese has browned.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and bake in jelly roll pan.
Cool completely.
Combine remaining ingredients except frosting, and beat 10 to 15 minutes until light and fluffy.
Spread over cooled cake.
Top with frosting.

title: apple dip
directions: Cream with mixer. Wonderful to dip sliced apples or other fruits. Refrigerate until needed.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat egg yolks and add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla, salt, flour and baking powder.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in 10 x 18-inch pan and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Take from pan onto cloth dusted with confectioners sugar.
Spread with jelly, roll up and cool.

title: colonial pumpkin bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in pumpkin and eggs. Add combined dry ingredients and mix well. Spread mixture into greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: southern potato salad(makes about 5 cups.)
directions: In large bowl, combine ingredients. Mix well. Cover and chill. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: hot dipping pizza sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low heat to simmering.
Keep warm while serving.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Beat egg
into	cold ice water and vinegar.
Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut
in	Crisco	and
add
the egg, water and vinegar. This makes 5 single crusts.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Measure dry ingredients into shallow bowl. Add onion juice and vinegar. Add oil gradually with whisk. Stir in seeds or can put all in glass jar and shake.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on 6 English muffins cut in half.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour, then cut each in half and then in fourths. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: pea soup
directions: Combine ingredients.
Season mixture with pepper.
Simmer, covered, over low heat, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; blend well.
Add vanilla wafers and milk alternately.
Fold in coconut, nuts and pineapple.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: creole black eyed peas
directions: Spray dutch oven with butter flavored spray.
Saute all ingredients together except rice.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: strawberry crumble
directions: Beat 20 minutes at moderate speed.
Add whipped topping and blend for 5 more minutes.
Put half bread crumb crust on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon strawberry mixture on top.
Sprinkle other half crumb crust on top.
Freeze several hours or overnight.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape in baking dish.
Put 3 onions, 3 potatoes and 3 carrots around it.
(Depending on size of potatoes and onions, cut in half or quarters).
Cut carrots into sticks and add salt and pepper over vegetables.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes to brown.

title: my best meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Shape into loaf in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 cup ketchup and sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar (optional).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook
spaghetti according to package directions; drain. (Should
have
about 3 cups cooked spaghetti.) Stir margarine, Parmesan
cheese
and eggs into hot spaghetti.
Form spaghetti mixture
into
a
"crust"
in
a
buttered	10-inch pie plate. Spread cottage cheese over bottom of spaghetti crust.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Saute onion until tender in butter in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients (except beef).
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Makes 2 cups.
Cut beef into strips; brown in butter.
Add to sauce.
Simmer.
Good served on rice.

title: weight watchers banana split cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Press graham crackers into pan.
Layer with pudding, bananas, Cool Whip, strawberries and pineapple (in that order).
Sprinkle coconut on top (optional).

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar, and spread on pizza pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°, until light brown.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust. Mix strawberries and glaze and spread mixture over the cream cheese mixture layer.

title: creamy egg nog pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine pudding mix, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and egg nog; mix well.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in rum.
Cool or chill thoroughly.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream (ready made may be substituted).
Spoon into pie shell or crust. Garnish with additional nutmeg.
Chill 4 hours, or until set. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream 2 sticks margarine with Crisco.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1 1/2 cups flour, 1/2 cup milk and 2 eggs.
Mix well.
Add another 1/2 cup milk, 1 1/2 cups flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar and salt.
Mix well again.
Add walnuts and vanilla.
Bake in prepared tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.
Then bake for 30 more minutes to brown, at 350°.

title: cabbage and kielbasa
directions: In a heavy pan, combine cabbage, onion and sausage.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 20 minutes or until cabbage is done.
Stir in sour cream, mustard, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: split pea with ham soup
directions: Let peas soak 1 hour.
Mix all ingredients together in 2 quarts water and simmer.
Let simmer 2 hours.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Gradually add sugar; beat until thickened. Add milk, half and half, cream, vanilla and salt.
Mix thoroughly. Chill. Churn freeze.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except catsup. Spread mixture in ungreased loaf pan or shape into loaf in a rectangular ungreased pan.
Spoon catsup over the top. Bake, uncovered at 350° until done (1 to 1 1/4 hours).

title: fudge cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, cocoa, butter and milk and bring to a boil.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter or nuts.
Add vanilla and oats.
Beat until thick and spoon on wax paper.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar until dissolved.
Add pepper and boil hard 1 minute. Remove from heat, add few drops green food coloring and Certo.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Pour into jars.

title: tomi's veggie sandwich
directions: French's| GourMayo has other flavors if you prefer something instead of horseradish.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans together and pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° until light brown.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel and cream avocados.
Mix
in
rest of ingredients. Chill and serve.
May be served on salad or served with chips.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk and spice.
Fill a baked pie shell. Let set about 15 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: baked zita
directions: Combine zita with Ricotta cheese, egg, parsley, salt and pepper.
Spread a layer of spaghetti sauce on bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Put 1/2 of zita mixture on top, another layer of sauce and rest of zita.
Top with sauce; sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Cover; bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown the meat in hot fat.
Add 2 cups water and simmer about 45 minutes.
Cook celery until tender.
Add the meat and broth to the celery.
Add vegetables, mushroom soup and the soy sauce. Bring to boil and thicken with flour and water.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over rice or chow mein noodles.
Sprinkle with more soy sauce.
Chicken, turkey or hamburger may be substituted for the steak, but use 1 cup broth with it.
Serves about 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In large pot, combine raw chicken, celery, 1 cut-up carrot, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover with water.
Cook until done. (Stewing chicken takes 2 or more hours; broiler-type chicken or fryer takes 1 hour or more.)
Cool and remove excess meat from bones.
Save broth (remove fat, if excessive, by refrigerating until fat hardens and remove).

title: strawberry chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Prepare pastry crust and set aside.
Beat cream cheese and sugar in a large mixer bowl until smooth.
Puree strawberries with syrup in food processor or blender.
Add to cream cheese mixture. Blend in flour, eggs, strawberry extract and food color.
Stir in mini chips chocolates.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Without opening oven door, decrease temperature to 250° and continue to bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until set.
Cool. Loosen cake from side of pan.
Cover; chill several hours or overnight.
Serve topped with sweetened whipped cream and strawberries.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pasta overnight salad pepe
directions: Prepare pasta, drain and cool.
Drain pineapple and save the juice.
Drain fruit cocktail, juice not saved.
In a saucepan mix eggs, sugar, flour, salt and pineapple juice.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Pour over pasta.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, whip cream and fold in pasta mixture.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and fruit cocktail, fresh strawberries or bananas may be added just before serving.

title: french beans
directions: Let beans come to boil in own juice; drain.
Put in casserole. Cover with sliced onion and crumble bacon over.
Let sugar and vinegar come to boil.
Add 1 tablespoon bacon drippings.
Pour over beans and let stand in warm place 3 to 4 hours.
Pour off before serving.

title: cocoa peanut butter chip pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle chips in bottom of crust.
Melt butter in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Add cocoa and stir until smooth.
Add milk and water.
Stir with a whisk until blended.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Remove from heat and pour into crust.
Bake 30 minutes or until edges are set. The center will set while cooling.
Garnish with topping.

title: seafood for patty shells
directions: Saute celery and peppers in butter until tender.
Add flour and cook until smooth.
Remove from heat and blend in milk. Cook until thickened. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat, stirring until cheese is melted and seafood is hot.
Spoon into baked patty shells. Makes an excellent lunch.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients except mushrooms.
Mix well.
Fill each cap with 1 teaspoon of filling.
Place in pan, stuffing side up. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: new fashioned corn relish
directions: Combine onion, vinegar, sugar and celery seed in saucepan; bring to boil, turn down heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine corn and remaining ingredients.
Pour hot mixture over the corn mixture, mix and cool.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Makes 3 cups.

title: big soft ginger cookies
directions: Mix all but 2 tablespoons sugar.
Shape into balls of about 1 heaping tablespoon size.
Roll in the 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven about 10 minutes.
(Do not overcook, just until puffed and light brown.)
Makes 24 three-inch cookies.

title: dodo's green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter or oleo until clear, not brown.
Place 1 can beans in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer onions, pimentos, cheese, water chestnuts and a few almonds.
Repeat beans and rest of ingredients.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Cover first 15 minutes.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and cook over medium heat until it boils, remove from heat.
Mix together next five ingredients.
Grease pan with thin layer of sauce, 1/2 pound sliced Mozzarella cheese, 1/2 package uncooked lasagne noodles.
Layer noodles, 1/2 spinach and cheese mixture, 1/2 sauce mixture, then repeat with other 1/2 of mixtures.
Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover pan with foil and bake 1 hour.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: kay's banana muffins
directions: Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: corn chowder
directions: Bring water, potatoes and onion to boil in large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once or twice, until potatoes are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt stick of oleo and pour over dressing.
Mix rest of ingredients and add to stuffing mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Size of pan depends on how thick you want the casserole.
I use zucchini squash.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together, drain grease.
Add rest of ingredients and cook 15 minutes or until macaroni is done.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Let cool.
Split layer for icing.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
(Note: Reserve 1 cup sour cream mix for frosting.)
Spread remaining mixture between layers.
Combine reserved mixture with whipped topping. Ice the cake.
Place in a sealed container.
Refrigerate for 3 days.

title: pork chops - dogpatch style
directions: Trim a little fat from the edge of the chops and fry out in a heavy skillet.
Remove pieces.
Flour chops and brown in the hot fat.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon fat from skillet and pour catsup mixture over and around chops.
Cover and cook over low heat 1 1/4 hours or until very tender.
Spoon sauce over chops once or twice during cooking and add a little water as needed.
Serve chops and sauce with cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except the bacon.
Put into a long baking dish.
Top with bacon, cut into small pieces.
Bake at 350° until the bacon is done.

title: peanut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
On low speed, beat brown sugar, flour, salt, half and half and vanilla until well blended.
Beat in eggs and peanut butter.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle peanuts on top. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until filling is puffy and center is set.

title: peanut chocolate parfait dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour bottom only of 9 x 13 inch pan.
In large bowl, combine all crust ingredients at medium speed until well blended.
Spread evenly in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes.
DO NOT OVERBAKE.
Cool.

title: mom's chili
directions: In a large pot, brown ground beef and saute the onion and green peppers.
Drain off the grease.
Add the peeled tomatoes and red kidney beans; cook on low heat for about 1 hour or more.
Put in chili powder; adjust to taste.
For toppings, use raw onion and Cheddar cheese (shredded).

title: paper cup salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add well drained fruit cocktail, well drained pineapple, diced banana and nuts.
Spoon into paper cups in muffin pans.
Freeze.
Remove from tins and store in freezer in covered container.

title: velvet crumb cake
directions: Heat oven to 350. Grease and flour square pan, 8 x 8 x 2 inches or 9 inch round pan. Beat all ingredients except topping on low speed, scrapping bowl constantly, 30 seconds. Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 4 minutes. Pour into pan. Bake until wooden pick inserted in middle comes out clean, 30-35 minutes. Cool slightly, spread with topping. Set oven control to broil and/or 550°. Broil about 3 inches from heat until golden brown, about 3 minutes.

title: lasagna(spicy)
directions: Brown meat; add tomatoes, tomato sauce, taco mix and garlic. Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles and rinse in cold water.
Layer as follows:
1/2 noodles, 1/3 sauce, 1/2 Mozzarella, 1/2 cottage cheese, 1/2 noodles, 1/3 sauce, 1/2 Mozzarella, 1/2 cottage cheese and rest of sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: sour cream rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
To the cooked rice, add chilies, cheese and sour cream.
Add salt and pepper. Butter casserole dish.
Pour in rice mixture; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wild rice pecan
directions: In small saucepan, bring 2 1/2 cups of water to a boil and stir in 1/2 teaspoon of the salt and the wild rice.
Lower the heat and simmer 45 minutes.
About halfway through cooking time, bring the remaining water to a boil in a separate saucepan, then add the remaining salt and the long grain rice.
Bring to a boil and lower heat to simmer for about 18 minutes.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix together.
Put into graham cracker crust.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Let stand at room temperature for two hours.

title: raspberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; set aside to cool.
Add cream cheese, pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Slowly heat soup, half and half and butter.
Saute bacon with onion until crisp.
Chop bacon and add to soup mixture.
Add garlic, salt, white pepper and Beau Monde seasoning to taste. Simmer on low.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Stir in ingredients.
Shape into ball. Chill, then roll in chopped nuts.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Combine flour, oats, cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts.
Cut in butter.
Place fruit in pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Crumble and sprinkle oat mixture over fruit.
Cover well with the mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Slice chicken into 1-inch chunks.
Pour dressing over chicken just to cover and allow to marinate for a few minutes.
Heat skillet and place chicken and all of marinade mixture into skillet. Saute over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes; cut into a chicken piece with a sharp knife.
If it is white inside, remove from heat immediately.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: low fat banana pudding
directions: In a 4 quart bowl arrange wafers and sliced bananas topped with pudding mixture until the bowl is full.
Cover the top of the finished pudding with a finishing layer of vanilla wafers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 1 hour or less.

title: "easy" chile
directions: *The amount of chili powder and jalapeno peppers depends on how hot you like it!

title: cranberry (sauce)-apple gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Break up jellied cranberry sauce with fork; add to gelatin mixture.
Chill until very thick before folding in apples.
Peel apples and finely grate.
Fold apples into mixture.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Serves 6.

title: old fashion cookies
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Drop and bake at 375°.

title: coffee-toffee bars
directions: Cream
margarine
and
brown sugar.
Add almond extract, salt, instant coffee, baking powder and flour.
Mix all together
to stiff
dough.
Spread in greased jelly roll pan (cookie sheet with sides).
Sprinkle with 1 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Press into dough (it will be thin).
Bake at 325°
for
12 to 15 minutes.
Don't burn.
Cut immediately into squares before cooling.

title: microwave tea
directions: Place cold water and tea bags in center of microwave. Heat on HIGH for 4 minutes. Let steep for 5 minutes. Add a small pinch of baking soda and gently stir. Remove bags and add the liquid to 3 1/2-quarts cold water. Stir in sugar and stir until dissolved. Serve over ice.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Arrange chicken in greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Put cheese slices on chicken.
Mix soup with sherry.
Pour over cheese.
Mix stuffing with oleo and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Yum! Yum!

title: peanut butter shortcake
directions: Bring to a boil oleo, water and peanut butter.
In a large mixing bowl, put flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Pour in hot mixture and mix.
Add eggs and sour cream and mix well.
Pour into well-greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: market salad
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together first five ingredients.
Add vegetables.
Toss thoroughly to blend.
Add cheese.
Toss lightly. Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: nonhardening no-cook play dough
directions: Mix and knead.
Can be colored with food coloring.

title: sunday brunch casserole
directions: Spray Pam in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Layer bread cubes, sausage, mushrooms and cheese. Mix the eggs, 2 cups milk, salt, pepper and mustard and pour over the layered ingredients. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Just before baking, mix the soup with the remaining milk and pour over the top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let it stand for 15 minutes before cutting into squares for serving. Serves 12.

title: patricia's fried fish
directions: Soak fish, covered with water plus 1/2 cup vinegar, for 30 minutes. Drain and rinse.
Combine flour, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Cook fish fillets until golden on both sides. Drain in wire basket.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix well and bake in unbaked pie shell until set.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop ingredients very fine; salt and pepper to taste.
Combine mayonnaise, milk and sugar or Sugar Twin (sweeten to your taste). Add celery seed and vinegar.
Beat well and pour over cabbage mixture.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in sugar.
Cool and add eggs.
Stir well and add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10 x 15 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut in squares while warm.
Before cooking, add chocolate chips to top of batter if desired.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Cut steak in long pieces, about 1 1/2 x 3-inches.
Put about 1 or 2 tablespoons of stuffing in center of meat and roll up and fasten with toothpick. In skillet brown roll-ups in oil.
Pour off excess oil.
Combine soup and water, add meat roll-ups.
Cover and cook over low heat 1 hour or until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Let set for 24 hours.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Place one can crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and vanilla until creamy. Spoon on top of dough.
Place 2nd can of rolls on top of cream cheese mixture.
Beat egg white and brush on top.
Cover with brown sugar and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grilled chicken salad
directions: Season to taste chicken; grill or pan saute until done.
Cut into strips.
Saute bacon in a separate pot.
Add honey Dijon; simmer 5 minutes.
Layer lettuce, eggs, chicken and cheese.
Cover with honey-bacon-Dijon dressing while warm.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce, water and oregano in a bowl.
In another bowl, mix together 1 cup Mozzarella, Parmesan, cottage cheese and eggs.

title: mikey's cheesy tost
directions: Tost bread, a peace of cheese on tost on for sauce.
Put tost in microwave.
Heat for 24 seconds or until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter chex munchies
directions: Melt peanut butter, chips and butter over low heat.
Pour over Chex that have been placed in large bowl or pan with lid. After coating, add powdered sugar.
Cover container with lid and shake well.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; roll into balls.
Freeze.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy tomato onion vinaigrette
directions: Combine the sugar, vinegar, onions, spaghetti sauce mix, and honey in blender.
Blend well. Slowly add oil and blend well. stir in poppy seed.
When refrigerated, this dressing sometimes separates with oil on bottom.
Simply shake well and enjoy!

title: camp fry bread
directions: Mix the above ingredients.
Add warm water to form a dough. Knead until dough is soft and not sticky.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Shape into balls with hand; pat flat to 1/4-inch thickness. Put 1/2-inch shortening in heavy skillet.
Brown on both sides and drain on paper towels.

title: strawberry bonanza
directions: Combine powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Use a little cold milk; pour into crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Pour strawberry mixture over that.
Top with whipped cream.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes until done.
Scoop out potato from skin. Combine potato pulp, sour cream and remaining ingredients, except cheese, in small bowl.
Beat at medium speed just until potato lumps disappear.
Do not overbeat.
Stuff shells with potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: nachos with beans and cheese
directions: Drain hot cooked pinto beans and mash with potato masher. Spread beans on tortilla triangles; top with thin slice of cheese and slice of jalapeno pepper.
Put under broiler until cheese is melted.

title: our favorite meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Pour milk over bread crumbs; add ground beef, salt, pepper, carrot, onion and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Mix ketchup, brown sugar and mustard; spread mixture on meat loaf.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Makes eight servings.

title: hojalda(fried bread)
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix egg, oil and milk.
Add flour and mix well.
Flour a large piece of waxed paper.
Remove from bowl and knead for about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle on flour as needed.
If ingredients become too dry, wet hands with oil.
Work into a roll and place in an empty bread sack and let set overnight.
Heat oil in a large pan or kettle.
Cut into pieces.
Stretch a little and deep fry until a light brown color.

title: cold tomato cocktail
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Strain and serve in juice glasses.

title: heavenly delight salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O.
If you use fruit cocktail juice and add water to make proper amount of liquid, this is much tastier.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Combine Jell-O and Dream Whip in pan.
Thoroughly blend with mixer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Over this, pour fruit cocktail.
Top with cherries.
Chill until set.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: tea fruit punch
directions: Mix together the water and iced tea mix, then add orange and cranberry juice.

title: springtime garden dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Combine all ingredients in bowl, mix well.
Serve with cut fresh veggies or crackers.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, using only a little of the pecans. Chill. Shape into a ball and roll in remaining pecans. Serve with crackers. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: coca-cola pork chops
directions: Place chops in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in a single layer and salt to taste. Mix ketchup and 1/2 Coke well and pour over chops, then pour remaining Coke over this. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until liquid is thick.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Cover raisins with water; bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes. Drain raisins, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Cool raisins and liquid thoroughly. Sift together flour, soda, salt and spice. Cream together shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold raisins into batter. Blend in flour mixture alternately with raisin liquid, beating well after each addition. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top cake with icing (confectioners sugar, cream cheese and lemon flavoring).

title: squash patties
directions: Combine squash, onion and green pepper in a medium saucepan. Add water to cover.
Cook over medium heat until tender; drain. Add next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until browned.
Yields 10 to 12 patties.

title: deep gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and one egg well.
Pat with hands into 13 x 9-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese and eggs.
Beat 5 minutes and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Dust with reserved sugar while hot.

title: eggplant plus
directions: Cover eggplant with cold water and soak 15 minutes; drain and turn into a buttered 2-quart round casserole (8 x 2-inches).
Pour sauce mix (just as it comes from ts envelope) over eggplant; toss lightly.
Arrange tomatoes over eggplant.
Bake, covered, in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes, stirring twice.
Uncover, sprinkle with cheese and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: chocolate chip protein cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly coat baking sheet with cooking spray.
In a small bowl, mix together flour, protein powder, baking powder, salt and chocolate chips.
In a large bowl, combine fructose and brown sugar.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until mixed.
Add butter and beat until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add vanilla extract.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients and beat until blended.
DO NOT OVERMIX.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 1 minute before removing from baking sheet. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: old settlers' beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Do not drain beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, eggs and oil together.
Spread 1/2 of batter in a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been greased and floured. Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle 1/2 of mixture over cake batter in pan.
Pour remaining batter in pan, then sprinkle rest of cinnamon mixture over top.
Swirl cinnamon through cake batter with knife blade.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: cranberry ring
directions: Add jello to hot cranberry juice.
Cool, then add lemon juice. Fold in celery, apples and nuts.
Pour into ring mold and chill. Unmold on crisp lettuce to serve.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together well beaten eggs, oleo, sugars, vanilla and peanut butter.
Then add rest of everything.
Mix by hand when everything is together (your hands).
Mix well.
Be sure to soften peanut butter, if it is refrigerated.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
They spread so don't make them very large.

title: hearty minestrone soup
directions: In a large pot, brown the bacon with the onion and celery. Add the garlic and basil and saute until vegetables are tender. Add soups, water and tomatoes.
The tomatoes should be cut up a bit, but make sure all the juice goes into the soup.
Bring to a boil.
Add ditalini, zucchini and cabbage.
Cover and reduce heat. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare, core and cut apples into slices.
Arrange in pie shell. Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
(This will take about 2 months.)
Cut vegetables into cubes (another 2 months).
Place meat in pan and cover with 1000 gallons of brown gravy.
Simmer for 4 weeks.
Shovel in salt and pepper to taste.
When meat is tender, add vegetables (steam shovel is useful here).
Simmer slowly for 4 weeks.
If more are expected, add the rabbit.
(This isn't recommended, as few people like hare in their stew.)

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Peel potatoes and slice about 1/2-inch slices.
Put in bottom of long pan.
Slice onions in rings on top of potatoes.
Put chops on this.
Heat cream of chicken soup until smooth.
Pour over chops.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil and bake until chops are done at 350°.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sift flour and salt together.
Combine the next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add 1/4 cup of flour mixture.
Toss to coat evenly and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar gradually, beating until light.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine soda and buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour mix.
Add candy mixture.
Beat well.
Spoon into a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: ham jambalaya
directions: Spray a large frying pan with Pam.
Saute onions, pepper, celery and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients (except rice).
Bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Reduce heat and simmer for 40 minutes or until rice is tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Contains 1020 mg. sodium, 230 calories, 16 g. protein, 31 g. carbohydrates, 4 g. fat and 30 mg cholesterol.

title: garlic chicken and pasta
directions: Heat butter in skillet, add chicken and saute until chicken is cooked.
add mushrooms, onions, and garlic.
Saute until soft. Add cream and heat to a low boil.
Sauce will thicken in about 5 minutes.
Add parmesan cheese, frozen peas and parsley.
Heat until peas are just tender.
Cook pasta.
Drain and rinse pasta well.
Put pasta in a large serving bowl.
Pour sauce over pasta. Serve with extra parmesan cheese and garlic bread.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix well the cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pinch up 1/2-inch ridge around all sides.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Mix at high speed.
Pour over cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: amish half-a-pound cake
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine all the ingredients at once, beating them together on medium speed for 20 minutes.
Pour the batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan and place in cold oven.
Set the oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour.
Remove the cake from the oven.
Immediately invert onto a wire rack and tip it out.
If cake sticks, loosen from sides with a knife and whack on counter to shake it loose.
Cool completely before serving. "Enjoy."

title: apple pancakes
directions: Mix pancake mix according to directions. Stir in applesauce until lumps disappear.
Cook on skillet.
Spread on apple butter. Eat it all up.
Yum! Yum!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli as package directs; drain.
Mix with mushroom soup, onion and mayonnaise.
Place in casserole dish. Top with cheese, then croutons.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until brown.

title: golamki casserole
directions: Saute onions and add rice and brown.
Brown ground beef.
Mix together salt, pepper, water and tomato sauce.
Heat to boiling.

title: hershey pie
directions: Put in double boiler and heat until dissolved.
Add 6 almond Hershey bars.
Stir until well blended.
Cool thoroughly.
Whip 1 cup of cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into graham cracker shell.
Put some crumbs on top.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cheese.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Place boneless meat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add onion and pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Crumble 1/2 of the bag of Doritos and sprinkle over meat.
Mix the soups, broth, Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese together. Warm over medium heat.
Mix well and pour over chicken and Doritos.
Add other 1/2 of Doritos and bake at 375° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: fiesta punch
directions: Combine drink mixes.
Add sugar, lemonade, juice and water. Makes 1 gallon.
Freeze 2 cups of extra pineapple juice in plastic containers to use in punch bowl instead of blocked ice.

title: seafood crepes
directions: Prepare crepes.
Cook and stir mushrooms and 2 tablespoons onions in margarine until onions are tender.
Stir in seafood, half and half and cream cheese.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Spoon 1/4 of the filling down center of each crepe; roll up.
Place in ungreased rectangular microwavable dish, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inches.
Sprinkle with Swiss cheese.
Microwave uncovered on High (100%) until cheese is melted and crepes are heated through, 4 to 6 minutes; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons onion.

title: mel's crab cakes
directions: Pick crabmeat.
Put aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over crabmeat.
Fold together and make cakes. Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours before frying. Fry or broil until brown.

title: sunshine dip
directions: Mix the peanut butter, honey and butter until you have gotten all the lumps out.
Once it is nice and creamy, take bread and dip it into the mixture.

title: strawberry-banana dessert
directions: Layer ingredients as follows:
Crumbled angel food cake, 3 bananas (sliced), 2 boxes strawberries, 1/2 pudding and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate.

title: corn souffle
directions: Melt butter; add flour and mix to a smooth paste.
Add milk and corn; cook until thick, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add beaten egg yolks, salt, cheese and green pepper.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites; pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: tofu chili
directions: Heat oil and saute onion until tender.
Add garlic, tofu and seasoning.
Stir in tomato paste and vinegar.
Cook over low heat for a few minutes.
Add beans and water.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Vegetables such as peppers, zucchini, corn or cabbage may be added.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix all together except for chips, peanut butter and nuts. Press into buttered pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Melt chips and add peanut butter and nuts, if desired. Frost while hot.

title: half moon cookies
directions: With mixer, cream shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla.
In bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and sour mix alternately to creamed shortening mixture.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Frost 1/2 cookie with vanilla frosting and 1/2 cookie with chocolate frosting.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine corn meal sugar and salt.
Stir in boiling water. Allow to cool.
Stir in milk and Egg Beaters, then blend in baking powder.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.

title: sandy's pineapple cake
directions: Make cake as directed on package and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for about 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: spinach pie
directions: Pinch holes in 1 pie crust and bake at 375° until light brown. Cook chopped spinach as directed on box, then drain.
Beat 3 eggs and add to spinach.
Drain Ricotta, then add 3/4 to spinach.
Cut Mozzarella into cubes.
Add 3/4 to spinach.
Add grated cheese to mixture.
Place mixture into baked pie crust.
Top with thin layer of Ricotta and Mozzarella.
Cover with second pie shell and pinch holes (with fork).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: tropical muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in oleo with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add remaining ingredients and stir just until mixture forms a sticky dough and leaves sides of the bowl (do not overmix).
Spray 12 muffin pan cups (2 1/2 inches) with nonstick cooking spray.
Spoon an equal amount of pineapple mixture into each cup.
Bake until muffins are golden brown, 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove muffins to a wire rack and let cool.
Serve immediately or wrap individually and freeze until ready to use.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put in greased, floured pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into pan.
Freeze overnight. (Line pan with waxed paper or Saran Wrap if you want to unmold salad on plate.)

title: cavatini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, salt and onion. Add pepperoni, tomato sauce, Ragu spaghetti sauce, dry mix and water. Simmer. Cook pasta, drain and add to sauce. Place in a 9 x 13 greased pan and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered. (This tastes like you're eating spaghetti, lasagna and pizza all at the same time!)

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs, add rest of ingredients, except cinnamon.
Stir. Pour into 8-inch pie tin.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1/2 of the strawberries and place in saucepan. Add sugar, lemon juice and cornstarch. Cook on medium heat until thick.
Add rest of strawberries, either whole or cut up.
Cool and pour into pie shell.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: diabetes cookies
directions: Mix liquids.
Add soda to activate, then spices, then dry ingredients.
Mix in flour and raisins last.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and flatten a little before putting in oven.
Bake at 350° 8 to 10 minutes.

title: judy's cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add flour and soda.
Mix and add the semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.

title: better-than-sex cake(16 servings)
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a saucepan over medium heat, combine pineapple with juice, sugar, pudding and coconut.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Using a wooden spoon handle, poke holes in warm cake.
Slowly pour pineapple mixture over cake and spread evenly.
Cool.
Spread whipped topping evenly over cake and sprinkle with pecans.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: peanut butter chocolate pie
directions: Prepare pudding using half and half instead of package directions.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cut into pieces and add the peanut butter cups.
Pour into pie crust and freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: easy no bake rum balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into small balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Store in tight container.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix margarine, flour and chopped nuts together and press into 13 x 9-inch pan for the crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then let it cool.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg well.
Add sugar and beat until light and creamy. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to the egg and sugar. Beat well and add the apples, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a well buttered baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes in a slow oven at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: dorothy's carrot soup
directions: Peel and chop carrots and onion.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add carrots and onion.
Cover; steam and stir for 20 minutes, then add the broth and boil for 45 minutes.
When tender, blend in mixer along with liquid puree.
Heat to boiling, then serve.
Freezes well.
Makes 4 bowls.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add raisins, nuts, melted butter, applesauce and cherries.
Beat until well blended.
Grease tube pan and put wax paper on the bottom of the pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken pie
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add flour, stirring until well blended.
Slowly add 2 cups of broth, cooking until thickened and smooth.
Season with salt and pepper, then set aside.

title: aunt sugar's yam pone
directions: Peel yams and grate medium fine; there should be 4 cups slightly packed down.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; put with margarine and milk in boiler; let come to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Add oats and simmer for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter.
Drop on wax paper and let cool.

title: pineapple cake(no mixer, mix by hand)
directions: Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: clam spread
directions: Saute onions and pepper in melted butter.
Add clams with liquid and spices.
Add 1/2 cup bread crumbs (or more) until mixture is of spreading consistency.
Spread in a 9-inch pie plate or quiche pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and paprika.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat. Add seasonings and cabbage. Cook about 15 minutes. Place in casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: coconut pie crust
directions: Combine in bowl.
Press thin on 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: cheese-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut ends from mushroom stems.
Remove stems from mushrooms; chop stems finely.
Cook and stir mushroom stems, green onions and garlic in margarine until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Fill mushroom caps with stuffing mixture.
Place mushrooms filled side up in greased baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Boil water, oleo and salt.
Stir in flour and eggs until smooth.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cream together the cream cheese, pudding and the milk.
Pour on crust.
Top with Cool Whip. Drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain, peel and slice into a large bowl.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Saute onion and celery until soft.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, pepper, vinegar and water.
Cook.
Stir constantly until mixture is thick.
Pour over potatoes and toss.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over top.
Serve warm or cold.

title: crystal solution(children's; do not eat!)
directions: Mix together in container.
Place absorbent material (sponge or blotter) in container.
Watch it grow.

title: pepper steak
directions: Pound
steak
with
meat mallot and cut in serving size pieces.
Roll
in
flour.
Brown
meat in skillet and place in ovenproof
casserole
dish.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over steak.
Put cover on dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour and lower heat to 250° and bake for another hour.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease casserole lightly.
Cube bread.
Beat eggs; gradually add sugar, flour, salt and crushed pineapple, juice and all.
Mix all together and put into casserole, then put bread cubes on top. Then slice 1 stick of butter over all.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 400° uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8 (in an 8 x 8-inch pan). Excellent with ham or as a side dish.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into a lightly greased casserole or pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 minutes. Remove.
Put grated cheese on top, then cook an additional 10 or 15 minutes until cheese melts and is bubbly hot.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Add syrup to sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Take off burner and mix in peanut butter, Spanish peanuts and Special K cereal.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: light and fruity
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add ice cubes until most of the ice is dissolved.
Remove excess pieces of ice.
Add Cool Whip and blend with mixer.
Pour over graham cracker crust and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: pizza roll
directions: Chop onion and green pepper; fry with hamburger.
Add tomato paste.
Spread thawed dough in a cookie sheet.
Spread mixture on dough and top with cheese.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Brush with egg yolk.
Bake at 350° until golden, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Beat egg well; add crumbled yeast, sugar and salt.
Add Crisco.
Then add flour and milk gradually.
Knead lightly.
Let rise, then knead down and make rolls.
Let rise and bake in hot oven.
Leftover dough may be put in bowl, covered and refrigerated until the next day.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots and cool.
Mix sugar, oil and vinegar and bring to boil.
Cool completely.
Pour over carrots, onion and pepper. Chill well before serving.

title: potato skins
directions: Cut baked potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out the insides, leaving a thin layer of potato in skin.
Cut shells in half again lengthwise.
Brush with butter and seasonings.
Add toppings if desired and broil until brown, about 5 minutes.
Makes 16 potato skins.

title: sweet and sour cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; gradually stir in 1 cup pecans, pepper, pineapple, seasoning salt and onion.
Chill.
Form into a ball and roll in pecans.
(For fancy affairs, garnish with cherries, sliced pineapple and parsley.)

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix milk and egg yolks together.
Add butter and vanilla. Add creamed mixture to dry ingredients. Cook in double boiler until thick and smooth.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: easy pickled peaches
directions: Drain peaches.
Add remaining ingredients to juice and boil 5 minutes.
Add peaches and simmer 5 minutes.

title: golden cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Grease and flour a square 8 x 8 x 2-inch or a 9 x 9 x 2-inch (double recipe 9 x 13-inch) pan.
Measure all ingredients about 20 seconds.

title: granny's tea cakes
directions: Mix ingredients with hands until all mixed together.
Let stand a few minutes.
Pinch off to make cookies.
Place in greased cookie sheets and put into preheated oven at 400°.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crispy corn dogs
directions: You will need 10 wooden skewers for this recipe.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo,
then add eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Dissolve soda in warm water.
Add to cream mixture, then add vanilla, salt and baking powder.
Add cream and flour alternately.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until brown.
Good with icing.

title: salmon balls
directions: Mix everything except walnuts and parsley.
Roll into balls.
In small bowl, mix walnuts and parsley.
Roll balls into walnut mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: georgia's egg custard
directions: In a medium size bowl, add all the ingredients.
Mix well. Beat at medium speed for approximately 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into ready made crust.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° to 375° for about 15 to 20 minutes, or until when a toothpick is inserted, toothpick comes out dry.
Brown top of pie to satisfaction. Double ingredients to make 2 pies.
Serves 5 to 10 people.

title: curried chicken rice salad
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth.
Mix celery, onion, curry powder, mustard, pepper, dash of salt, lemon juice, pineapple and some pineapple juice into mayonnaise.
Add to rice.
Fold in chicken and nuts and refrigerate overnight.
Save pineapple juice as the rice really absorbs moisture.
You may need to add more mayonnaise and pineapple juice before serving.

title: velveeta potatoes
directions: Combine and heat ingredients except potatoes.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes after it reaches a boil; drain well. Mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased casserole dish. For crunchy top, mix crushed cheese crackers with melted butter. Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: christmas eve punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, lemonade, water and juice from the orange together
and chill well.
When ready to serve, add the ice ring to a large punch bowl and pour juice mixture over it. Gently stir in
ginger ale, tonic water and champagne.
Makes about 7 quarts.

title: cherry pecan bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Stir in pie filling, milk, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Blend well and fold in nuts.
Bake in 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans (9 x 5-inches) for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cool on rack 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn out on rack top side up.
Good served with cream cheese as tea sandwiches.

title: super guacamole
directions: Cut avocados in half and remove the pit.
Mash the meat of avocado well with a fork and add other ingredients.
Mix well and refridgerate before serving.
You may substitute finely chopped green chili peppers for the chili powder.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks in large bowl.
Sift flour with baking powder and add alternately with milk and vanilla. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites last.
Bake in Bundt pan at 300° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: giblet gravy
directions: In a heavy skillet or saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour; blend and stir well until flour is medium brown.
(Do not let this mixture burn; stir constantly.)
Add poultry stock; blend and stir well.
Cook slowly until mixture begins to thicken.
Add chopped giblets, pepper and Accent; continue cooking and stirring.
Add chopped eggs; blend well until gravy becomes thick enough to serve over rice and dressing as desired.

title: layered dip
directions: Spread the following layers into glass 9 x 13 dish: cream cheese mixed with chopped green onions, peach, salsa, black beans, Mexican cheese blend.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Sort beans.
Put in kettle. Cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain.
Put fresh water with baking soda in over beans.
Cook 15 minutes. Drain again. Add fresh water and salt to taste. Cook until beans start to get tender.
Drain and reserve juice.
Put beans in 3-quart baking dish.
Add the brown sugar and mix well. Add chunks of bacon and mix. Add some bean juice and stir.
(Save rest of juice in case beans get too dry before they are done.)
Top with strips of bacon. Do not cover.
Bake 2 hours in a 425° oven or until beans get brown and juice cooks off. Makes 6.

title: american chow mein
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: the greatest appetizer ever
directions: *Harry and David's makes pepper-onion relish.

title: black raspberry pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Fill with raspberries. Mix sugar and flour.
Sprinkle over berries.
Dot with butter. Adjust top crust.
Make slit in top.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; toss with steak strips to coat thoroughly.
Put in crock-pot; add onion, garlic and 1/2 of the green peppers.
Combine tomatoes with beef base, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into crock-pot, cover and cook on low 8 to 9 hours.

title: cheese krispies
directions: In a large saucepan, over low heat, melt the cheese and margarine together.
Remove from heat; add flour.
Stir in Rice Krispies and mix thoroughly.
Roll into small balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and onion.
Add soups and water.
Simmer on low heat about 1 hour or 1 1/2 hours.
Break spaghetti into small pieces and cook according to directions.
Add to ground beef mixture.
Put into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and bake in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: leo's delights
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients together.
Top muffins or Triscuits. Broil until bubbles.

title: okra fritters
directions: Place beans in heavy large saucepan.
Cover with water and bring to boil.
Drain.
Return beans to pan.
Pour in water to cover by 2 to 3-inches.
Add all remaining ingredients except salt. Bring mixture to boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer until beans are very soft, adding more water as necessary to keep beans submerged, about 3 1/2 hours.
Season with salt and cook 15 minutes longer, uncovered, if beans are too liquid.
Let cool.
Chill overnight.
To serve, reheat beans over medium-low heat, stirring frequently.
Makes 10 servings.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull strawberries; pick over carefully to remove any imperfect ones.
Add sugar and let stand overnight or at least 2 hours, covered.
Drain off juice; add enough water to juice to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Blend cornstarch to paste with about 1/4 cup of the liquid in top of double boiler.
Add rest of liquid and cook over direct heat with constant stirring until sauce boils and is clear.
Place over boiling water.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; add lemon juice and fold in strawberries.
Cool to lukewarm before pouring into baked pastry shell.
Top with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add sour cream, soda and extract and beat well.
Add eggs 2 at a time and 1 cup flour and beat well after each addition.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix well.
Put in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl. Mix well. Cover, and chill. Serve as a sandwich spread or as a dip with crackers.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine veggies, soup, cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can of onions.
Put into casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, for 5 more minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese, Old English cheese, pineapple spread, garlic powder and onion.
Refrigerate 1 hour, then roll in a ball and roll in bacon bits.

title: louise's buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of lukewarm water with 1 tablespoon sugar until foamy.
Add 2 cups lukewarm water.
Mix together all ingredients.
Raise 2 hours, then knead down.
Raise a second time for about 1 hour.
Raise on cookie sheet another hour.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until done.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer.
Good served over rice.

title: dee's round steak
directions: Cut off all fat from meat.
Cut into strips 1/2 x 3-inches or so.
Brown meat in oil; add ginger, garlic and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat, cover pan and cook 1 hour.
Blend cornstarch with water and soy sauce; stir into pan.
Add green pepper; cook until sauce is thickened and clear.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and walnut sandwiches
directions: Put walnuts in pan and cover with water.
Bring to boil for 3 minutes.
Cool with running water.
Remove skins.
Drain on paper towel.
Place oil in skillet over low heat.
When hot, add walnuts.
Saute walnuts until they turn golden.
Remove from heat. Chop walnuts up fine.
Mix chicken, walnuts, celery, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Blend until it makes a spread.
Put on bread or crackers.
Makes 12 sandwiches.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Blanch slivered almonds.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together.
Cut in oleo until in fine particles.
Beat egg lightly with water and blend in dry mixture.
Roll in balls (teaspoon).
Dip part of ball in sesame seed.

title: sugar-free decaf ice tea
directions: Put tea bags in saucepan; cover with cold water.
Bring to boil, cover, turn off heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Strain tea into a gallon glass jar or pitcher.
Cover tea bags again with cold water; bring to a boil.
Let sit for 5 minutes; strain into jar.
Finish filling jar with cold water.
Add sweeteners; stir.

title: syrian beet salad
directions: Drain beets; measure juice.
Add water to drained beet juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Bring liquid to a boil and remove from heat.
Add lemon gelatin, sugar, vinegar and horseradish, stirring until gelatin and sugar have dissolved.
Add beets and turn into mold or dish; chill until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop, cook and drain broccoli well.
Melt cheese and 1/2 stick of margarine.
Put broccoli in a baking dish.
Pour melted cheese and margarine over it.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Melt remaining margarine and pour over crumbs.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cinderella slippers
directions: Cut edges off bread and slice each piece into 4 strips.
Pour Eagle Brand milk in a bowl and roll bread in milk.
Then roll in coconut.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: my mama's drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar, spices and flour together.
Add eggs and butter. When well mixed, add raisins, pecans and coconut.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: grandma elaine's popcorn
directions: Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons sugar and add a few drops of coloring.
Shake and pop.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Stir in rice, onion flakes, soup and water.
Arrange chicken over top of mixture. Sprinkle with coarse black pepper.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until sugar dissolves, then add to eggs. Add pecans, butter, vanilla and salt.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Cook 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and cook 20 minutes.

title: venison
directions: Wash meat thoroughly.
Remove all visible fat.
Soak overnight in salt, vinegar and water to cover meat and bay leaves.
Boil meat in same water until tender (do not overcook, approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Remove meat from pot liquor.
Place in baking dish. Season with remaining dry ingredients.
Place bacon strips, crosswise, on meat.
Bake at 350° until bacon is crisp.
Baste with small amounts of pot liquor, keeping baking dish moist at all times.
Spoon on brown sauce, barbecue, sweet and sour or other if desired.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
(rinse and chop spinach) and top with poppy seed dressing.
Serves 4.
Time of preparation: 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Mix by hand or mixer, adding flour gradually.
Divide and roll into about 1/4-inch thick and cut into wedges.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Watch closely as it gets brown in a hurry.

title: maryland crab imperial
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cream, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and capers.
Remove 1/4 of mixture.
Add crabmeat to remainder and blend lightly.
Divide into four clean crab shells or individual casseroles.
Top with remaining mixture. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes (until light brown and heated through).
Garnish with a sprig of parsley and lemon wedge.
Serves 4.

title: white brownies
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar, vanilla, and salt and mix well.
Beat in eggs, 2 at a time.
Add flour.
Grease 11 x 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Don't overbake. After cooled they can be frosted with chocolate frosting or eat plain.

title: easter bread
directions: Beat eggs, orange rind, lemon rind and juice.
Mix dry yeast with warm water in a bowl.
Mix all ingredients and gradually add the flour.
Knead dough. Cover and let rise 4 to 5 hours.
Shape into loaves.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: tropical oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars until creamy.
Add egg and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients and chocolate chips.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: for the crowd casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion.
cook until tender, but not done.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Place
eggs
in large bowl and beat slightly.
Stir
in corn syrup, melted chocolate, sugar, butter, vanilla and pecan halves. Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350°
in
preheated	oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until a
knife
inserted into center of the pie comes out clean.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugar and oleo.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well. Add vanilla.
Add sour cream and soda.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
Add to cream mixture.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Roll out and cut into shapes.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: angel salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Cool.
Warm cream cheese to room temperature.
Mash, adding pineapple and pecans.
Add to jello mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into jello mold.
Chill.

title: pecan pie 6
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine. Add salt, vanilla, eggs, flour and pecans.
Stir well and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Cook at 450° for 10 minutes and then at 350° for 25 minutes or until pie slightly shakes in center.

title: savory pumpkin pie
directions: Cut pumpkin in slices; peel, dice and cook in 1/3 cup water over moderate heat with chopped garlic for 20 minutes or until dry. Meanwhile, brown the bacon.
Drain the fat off and reserve.
Mix egg yolks with flour, cream and milk.
Add chopped chives.
Oil lightly pie dish.
Place pie shell in a deep dish.
When pumpkin is cooked, puree it.
Add bacon and egg mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in hot oven.
Serve hot with salad.

title: perky potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes at least 1/2 hour, spreading out on paper towels.
Mix
all
ingredients
and
add
to
thawed potatoes. Place in
greased
x 12-inch pan and (optional) if desired, spread crushed
cornflakes over top for added crispness (I use Italian seasoned
bread
crumbs
on top instead of cornflakes, also extra grated
cheese
on
top).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Freezes well before baking.

title: overnight frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit and place in a large bowl.
Set aside.
In a double boiler, mix frozen orange juice and 2 cups of sugar.
Beat 2 eggs; pour in container with orange juice and sugar.
Cook until these ingredients are thick.
Should come to a rolling boil.
Set aside to cool.
After it has cooled, mix 8 ounces sour cream and 1 cup whipping cream.
Mix ingredients well.
Pour over fruit. Place in freezer and let freeze overnight.

title: pineapple pepper chicken
directions: In a saucepan, combine the first 10 ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Bring to a boil.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes until thick. Set aside.
Heat oil in skillet on medium heat.
Add the chicken; brown on all sides.
Place in 2 greased 13 x 9 x 2 dishes.
Pour reserved sauce over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add pineapple and green pepper.
Bake 15 minutes longer. Yield:
12 servings.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa and shortening.
Stir in beaten eggs, one at a time.
Add baking soda to buttermilk; add to creamed mixture alternately with flour and salt.
Mix well.
Stir but do not beat.
Add the cup of boiling water which will make a thin batter.
Add vanilla last.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch baking pan lined in the bottom with brown paper for about 45 minutes.

title: wadie's cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; sprinkle Accent on the cheese and Worcestershire sauce. Stir in onion and dried beef (saving enough beef to roll cheese ball in). Serve with crackers (apple slices or stuff celery).

title: play dough
directions: Combine ingredients in a Teflon pan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly. Dough will form into a ball while cooking. Store in an airtight container. Food coloring may be added to the recipe.
Fun for kids!

title: pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, soda, sugar and salt. Combine eggs, vinegar and milk. Stir until smooth. Add this mixture to the flour mixture. Add oleo.
Extra batter keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg, beaten light, vanilla and sour milk.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Spread rhubarb on top. Cover with topping of 1/2 cup of sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until done.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add dry Dream Whip and milk.
Mix and cream together real well.
Add sugar and vanilla.

title: chicken and rice balls
directions: Cook celery and onion in oleo until tender.
Cook rice in chicken bouillon.
Mix all but corn flakes and roll in balls, then in crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve sauce over balls.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Cook and drain enough macaroni to fill a medium size casserole 1/3 full.
Mix cheese, eggs and milk to macaroni while it is still hot from boiling.
Pour into casserole; cover with cheese (add sprinkles of chips, crushed, or crackers, crushed, if you want). Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes until cheese/milk is well set.
Then broil at 400° until brown on top.

title: snazzy dogs
directions: Combine corn chips, onion, tomato sauce, worcestershire sauce and cheese; mix well. Slice frankfurters lengthwise to make a pocket. Spoon stuffing mixture inside each pocket. Place frankfurters in a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan. Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese mixture is melted. Serve in hot dog buns.

title: pop's ugly apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Add topping while hot and return to oven.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil. Add tomatoes with remaining juice, salt and oregano. Cook over medium heat until liquid cooks down. Add cheese and cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring often. Add chopped chilies. Serve with tostados or corn chips.

title: taco mix
directions: Fry hamburger in oil until done; drain and add all other ingredients.
Simmer until celery and onions are done.
Serve with chips or taco shells.

title: key lime pie
directions: In a food processor, mix milk and cream cheese. Slowly add the lime juice. Mix for approximately 15 minutes. Pour into graham cracker crust. Top with Cool Whip.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix the ingredients in order given and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar and serve warm.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Warm the milk in a medium-sized saucepan over medium-low heat. Stir in rice. Bring to a simmer and cook, uncovered, stirring frequently, until the rice is very tender, about 35 minutes. In a medium-sized bowl, whisk together the egg, sugar, vanilla and salt. Gradually stir in some of the rice mixture until well blended. Return the mixture to the saucepan and stir over medium-low heat for 1 minute to cook the egg. Pour the mixture into 6 custard cups and sprinkle with cinnamon. Refrigerate for 1 hour or until chilled. Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal pumpkin bread
directions: Combine oats and milk in large bowl.
Allow to stand 5 minutes. Stir in pumpkin, egg whites and whole egg and melted margarine.
In separate bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Gradually add dry to oat mix, then stir in raisins and nuts and mix.
Bake in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan coated with nonstick vegetable spray and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Cook carrots and onion in 4 tablespoons oleo until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of stuffing cubes, soup and sour cream. Gently stir in zucchini.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt remaining oleo.
Add remaining stuffing cubes.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: wee wisdom chili
directions: Brown meat. Add ingredients. Cook to color. Add water.

title: fish stew
directions: Stir-fry vegetables until onion is translucent and cabbage has changed color.
Add water and consomme.
Add salt, peppercorns, hot sauce and cilantro.
Boil until vegetables are tender.
Add fish, return to boil and serve.

title: cool fruit dessert
directions: Mix pudding, use only 3 1/2 to 4 cups of milk.
Pudding will be thick.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Break cake in half.
Crumble 1/2 on bottom of oblong pan.
Spread 1/2 of pudding mixture over cake. Take 1/2 of each fruit and make a layer on top of pudding mixture. Repeat, starting with cake.
If desired, sprinkle with chopped nuts (pecans, walnuts) on last layer of fruit.

title: brown bread
directions: Boil raisins in 1 cup water.
Let cool.
Drain and save juice. Dissolve baking soda in juice from raisins.
Mix ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven in small greased loaf pan.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together. Pour into casserole dish.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shells.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet breakfast
directions: In skillet, cook sausage in small amount of water; drain. Add onion, green chiles (drained), 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper. Saut.
Remove meat mixture.
Melt butter; add hash browns. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt.
Press into pan lightly.
Add eggs. Spoon meat mixture in and sprinkle with cheese.
Cook on medium-low heat for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut and serve.
Serves 6.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix yeast and water in bowl.
Add sugar, salt and flour; mix well.
Knead on floured board.
Make 16 pieces.
Shape into pretzel.
Brush beaten egg on top of dough.
Sprinkle coarse salt. Spray cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy does it
directions: Mix all together and pour in Bundt pan.
Bake until brown on top at 350°.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all and heat in 350° oven until bubbly.
Serve on buttery crackers.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onion, bell pepper and green olives.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over this.

title: chocolate sheet cake(9 x 12-inch pan)
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Resift with salt and sugar.
In a saucepan, put oil, cocoa and water; bring to a boil.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture.
In another bowl, put eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add to flour mixture and mix well.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half and remove seeds.
Place squash, cut side up, in a shallow baking dish.
Add 1/2-inch boiling water to pan.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Beat sugar, flour, butter and eggs together.
Mix in rhubarb. Pour in a large unbaked pie crust.
Put lattice crust on top. Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg white very stiff.
Add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time and keep beating slowly.
Add vanilla and fold in nuts.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Be sure and line bottom of pan with tinfoil. Drop small amounts less than 1/2 teaspoon.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown onion and hamburger and add taco seasoning. Put meat mixture in tortillas and roll up. Lay them in 9 x 13 pan, seam side down. Combine remaining ingredients and cook over low heat until cheese is melted. Pour sauce over tortillas. Cover and bake for 40 minutes at 350° or until bubbly. These freeze well.

title: chicken adobo(nicole's favorite)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pot and let stand for at least 30 minutes.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat to simmer for an hour or until meat is tender.
Serve hot with rice.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar, salt, flour and well beaten egg yolks. Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water until thick and smooth.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 325° until slightly brown.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cover bottom of shallow baking pan with oil.
Bake potatoes for 30 to 35 minutes or until they are tender and golden.
