Mix Miracle Whip, eggs, bacon, onions, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Add potatoes; mix lightly.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit slush julius drink
directions: Combine in blender.
Cover; blend on high speed until smooth. If not thick enough, add more ice cubes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixing bowl, beat egg yolks, Eagle Brand milk, lime juice and just a bit of food coloring.
Pour into pie shell and bake 30 minutes.
Cool and chill.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate the leftover pie.

title: baked catfish or any kind of fish
directions: Mix all except butter.
Roll fish in butter then into crumb mixture.
Bake at 350 until brown.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream sugars and Crisco.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt and add to sugar mixture. Add oats slowly.
Add coconut, nuts and chocolate chips last.
By teaspoon, drop on cookie sheet, lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool a little before removing.
Yields 6 or 7 dozen.
(The waxed paper really does work.)

title: banana blitz
directions: Pour boiling water into blender.
Add gelatin and blend at low speed until completely dissolved, about 30 seconds.
Add ice cubes and stir until ice is partially melted.

title: zebra cookies
directions: Stir chocolate in small heavy saucepan over low heat until melted.

Cool. Combine eggs, sugar, melted chocolate, oil, baking powder and vanilla in a large bowl. Gradually add flour to chocolate mixture, stirring until combined. Cover and chill 2 hours or until easy to handle. Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls. Roll in powdered sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are set and tops cracked.
While still hot, press a kiss into center of each. Cool on a wire rack.
Makes about 48.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream together sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, beating well after each addition. Stir in apples.
Combine walnuts and 1 tablespoon flour.
Stir into batter.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan on rack.
Makes 9 servings.

title: white chocolate crunch
directions: Mix together the cereal, marshmallows and nuts in a large bowl.
Melt the white chocolate in double boiler.
Pour the melted chocolate over the cereal mixture and mix well with a big spoon. Pour into a lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut when cool.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well in large bowl and place in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Recipe can be prepared the day before serving and will also freeze.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat together the sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, soda and cinnamon (sifted).
Add vanilla, apples and walnuts.
Make a stiff dough.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: This basic recipe can be varied by adding a small amount of chopped spinach or cooked macaroni of your choice.

title: cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix condensed milk and cream cheese well.
Add lemon juice.
Spoon into graham cracker crust; chill. Spread cherry pie filling on top.

title: candied bananas
directions: Beat eggs.
Peel bananas and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Coat serving plate with sesame oil.
Dip banana pieces in flour, then coat with eggs.
Mix in dry flour again.
Deep fry bananas in 450° oil until golden brown; remove.
In another pan, heat 2 tablespoons oil, the sugar and the boiled water; stir over medium heat until sugar melts, then simmer over low heat.
Stir until it becomes caramel color.
Coat bananas with caramel and place on serving plate.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets and reserve beet liquid. Combine beet liquid and enough water to make 2 cups. Add salt, sugar, and vinegar to the liquid.
Stir.
Place mixture in a pan over low heat. Bring to a boil. Turn off stove; add cloves and pickling spice. Pour hot mixture over the sliced beets.
Let cool then cover and chill. Beets will keep several days in the refrigerator.
They are an excellent side for cabbage, green beans, and other country style cooked vegetables.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease	casserole.
Cream
butter,
sugar and eggs (use mixer).
Stir
pineapple and bread into mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cut English muffins in half.
Top muffin halves with pizza sauce, cheese, etc.
Microwave at 100% for 30 seconds or bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with strawberries and desired amount of glaze. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: poff loaf
directions: Cut pepperoni into small pieces.
Cook with ground beef and sausage in a large skillet.
Drain off all grease.
Add green chili peppers, cheese, onions and mushrooms.
Cook until cheese is melted and onions are tender.
When the dough has thawed, roll out the length of a long cookie sheet.
Spoon filling down the middle and close dough by wrapping.
Cook at 350° until light brown. Cook immediately after filling the loaf with mixture.
Do not let bread rise.

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Trim ends of eggplant and slice eggplant 1/4 inch thick. Brush with a little olive oil and place under broiler about 5 minutes per side.
Heat oven to 350°.
Layer ingredients in dish, a little sauce, eggplant cottage cheese, sauce, eggplant, both cheeses, sauce and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Bring milk just to a boil; remove from heat and add butter and salt.
Let set until lukewarm.
Mix together and add the warm water, yeast and sugar.
Mix and then stir in flour.
Mix and knead.
Let stand until doubled, 40 to 60 minutes.
Flatten out and spread with 1/4 cup soft butter.
Sprinkle with desired amount of sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch slices.
Rub butter on top.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mother's apple pie
directions: Combine apples and lemon juice in a large bowl.
Combine sugars, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg, mixing well.
Spoon over apple mixture, tossing gently.
Spoon filling evenly into pastry shell. Dot with butter.

title: black bean roll-ups
directions: Blend cream cheese, Monterey Jack cheese, sour cream and onion salt. Spread black beans, then cheese mixture on tortillas. Roll and refrigerate. Slice and serve with hot sauce.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onions and garlic in oil.
Add meat.
Brown.
Add mushrooms, tomato soup, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add sour cream just before serving.
Pour over rice or pasta.

title: cinnamon apple rings
directions: For syrup, in 10-inch skillet, combine water, candies and sugar.
Cook and stir over medium heat until candies dissolve and liquid boils.
Add apple rings to syrup.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender, stirring and spooning syrup over apples occasionally.
Cool apple rings in syrup.
Drain and serve. Makes about 3 cups.

title: favorite punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well; refrigerate.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring after each addition.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut while still warm.

title: potato chive casserole
directions: Cut potatoes in half (leave peelings on).
Put in salted water and boil until done.
Drain and put potatoes in long baking dish and chop.
Melt margarine and cheese.
Add sour cream and chives; salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well with potatoes.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs lengthwise into halves.
Slip out yolks; mash with fork.
Mix in mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.
Fill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it lightly.
Arrange eggs on large serving plate.
Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Makes 6 servings; contains 140 calories per serving.

title: praline biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 2 teaspoons butter, 2 teaspoons brown sugar and 3 pecans halves in each of 12 muffin cups (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches).
Sprinkle cinnamon in each cup; heat in oven until melted.
Mix baking mix, applesauce and milk until dough forms; beat 20 strokes.
Spoon into mixture in cups.
Bake 10 minutes. Invert on heatproof serving plate.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil to soft ball stage or 230°.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and nuts.
Beat and pour into greased pans.
Yield: 3 (8-inch) pie pans.

title: bananas flambe
directions: Melt butter in chafing dish and then brown sugar and stir until dissolved. Slice bananas in half lengthwise. Add bananas to brown sugar mixture and stir to coat. Cook bananas, stirring constantly for about 1 minute. Place individual portions of ice cream in separate serving dishes and get ready to serve. Add Kahlua to banana mixture and then light with match. Quickly spoon flaming banana mixture over each dish of ice cream and serve immediately.

title: fudge squares
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Remove from heat.
Add flour, cocoa and flour.
Mix well.
Add eggs, beaten with a fork.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and pecan pieces.
Mix again. Pour mixture into greased loaf cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat off.
Add onion, beans and tomato soup (undiluted).
Cook 15 minutes.
Add chili powder and continue cooking over low heat another 15 minutes.
(You may need to add a little water.)

title: hopping john
directions: Boil peas in salted water until tender. Add peas and 1 c. of the pea liquid to rice, bacon with grease and onion. Put in rice steamer or double boiler and cook for 1 hour or until rice is thoroughly done.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Combine berries, sugar, flour, lemon juice and salt.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Dot with oleo and top with the other pie shell.
Slit top 4 to 5 times for steam. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce temperature to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic until beef is brown.
Stir in soup and water.
Cook over low heat 45 minutes or until beef is tender.
Cook noodles according to package directions, drain. Just before serving add sour cream to beef mixture, stir and heat for 2 minutes.
Serve beef over hot noodles.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients after you have cooked and drained macaroni. Chill for 4 hours.

title: swedish apple pie(a crustless pie)
directions: Mix together dry ingredients. Add apples, nuts and egg.
Stir together.
Spread into 8-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes. Test apples for tenderness with toothpick.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Scrape and slice carrots in rounds and boil until tender. Drain and put in greased casserole.
Melt 1 stick margarine and Velveeta cheese in saucepan.
Pour over carrots.
Cut bread in cubes and mix in 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Put on top of carrots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cream dip
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and enough liquid to make a good dip.
Wash strawberries and let guest dip them in cheese mixture.
(I prefer to use milk and a dash of strawberry flavoring.)

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in mixing bowl.
Heat butter and Coke until boiling.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Batter will be thin with marshmallows floating on top.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: fettucini al alfredo with broccoli
directions: Cook fettucini according to package.
Add hot broccoli.
Add all ingredients and toss gently.

title: good luck pie crust
directions: With a fork, mix first 4 ingredients.
Beat remaining ingredients and combine the 2 mixtures.
Stir with a fork until moist throughout.
Using hands, mold into 5 balls.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Roll into a pie crust or freeze each ball for later.
Makes 5 crusts.

title: suzanne's crabmeat spread
directions: Mix cheese, horseradish and mayonnaise together.
Spread on serving dish with an edge.
Pour 3/4 bottle of cocktail sauce over cheese mix.
Crumble crabmeat on top.
Chill and serve with Triscuits.

title: texas chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish or pan. Mix soup, water and milk.
Heat and then pour over rice.
Place chicken pieces in pan with rice.
Sprinkle onion flakes, garlic powder and pepper over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pie crusts
directions: Mix flour and salt. Blend in oil with fork. Sprinkle water over mixture. Mix all together. With hands form into a ball, divide in half. Roll out on floured surface.

title: porter cake
directions: Rub butter into flour and add all other dry ingredients.
Blend very well.
Beat eggs with lukewarm Guinness and add bicarbonate of soda.
Mix this very well into dry cake mixture and turn into greased, lined cake tin, 9-inch diameter and 3-inches high.
Should be covered with grease-proof paper and baked at 200° to 250° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours, removing the paper for the last half-hour.
Test with skewer.
Makes a good Christmas cake.
If iced will keep well in a tin.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy peta bread cheese crisps
directions: Halve Syrian bread at edges (cut into circles, not across diagonally).
Liberally spread margarine on inside faces. Sprinkle with your own blend of cheese and seasonings for a variety of flavor combinations.
Cut into wedges.
Spread on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Store in airtight container and serve with dip or stand-alone chip.

title: oatmeal apple raisin muffins
directions: Grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper cups.
Prepare all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add chopped apples and raisins to dry mixture.
Beat egg, add oil and milk, then add to dry mixture, mixing just to moisten.
Spoon mixture into muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve piping hot or cool.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Cook 7 minutes; add almonds.
Put in casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pizza squash
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain well.
Mash squash with fork.
Over low heat, chop tomatoes into squash.
Add oregano, pepper and a little margarine.
Heat until warm.
Top with Mozzarella and melt in oven or microwave.

title: potato hot dish
directions: Cook in greased crock-pot.
Bake for 4 hours on high or 8 hours on low.
Serves 12.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Beat eggs, salt and flour (put all in together).
Store in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Best for 24 hours.
Take out and pinch off and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
I spray with Pam.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine, stirring well.
Spoon evenly over chicken and sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 to 55 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tommy's strawberry yum-yum
directions: Mix strawberries, Jell-O and sugar.
Use as layer over vanilla wafers.
Mix pudding, milk and sour cream and layer over strawberry layer.
Layer these 3 parts like banana pudding, then top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken and hot sausage bake
directions: Place potatoes in roasting pan.
Place chicken on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle with spices.
Put hot sausage on top of chicken.
Pour oil on top of sausage.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: zippy salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool and add other ingredients, stirring to blend them in.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
May be served on lettuce leaf with mayonnaise and paprika as a garnish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef and beer stew
directions: Coat beef cubes with flour and salt.
Saute mushrooms and onion in oil in large skillet.
Add meat and remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until meat is tender, checking to add water as needed.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: silky fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in a heavy saucepan over medium-low heat.
Stir in sugar, evaporated milk, corn syrup, and salt; cook over medium heat, stirring gently, 5 minutes or just until sugar dissolves and sauce is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Serve warm.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix.
After it's baked, pour Kahlua over it. Prepare pudding and refrigerate.
Crumble Heath bars.
Layer brownies, pudding, crumbled candy and Cool Whip, layer by layer, in a trifle bowl.
Top with maraschino cherries.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and chips on top of batter.
Bake at 300° for about 20 to 30 minutes. Let cool in pan and then cut into squares.

title: molasses cookies(drew's favorite cookies)
directions: Combine molasses, brown sugar, butter and shortening in large saucepan.
Heat, stirring until butter and shortening are melted. Mix baking soda and vinegar; stir into molasses mixture. Sift flour and salt together.
Gradually add to liquid mixture, blending with dough hooks after each addition.
Chill.
Roll out cut into shapes and decorate.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato-leek soup
directions: Put all ingredients into pot.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 to 12 hours.
If desired, mash potatoes with masher before serving.
Serve topped with chives.

title: spicy pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed of an electric mixer until foamy. Add sugar, oil and vanilla; beat 2 minutes, or until mixture is slightly thickened.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine flours and next 5 ingredients; add to zucchini mixture, stirring just until blended.
Stir in pecans and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased and floured
8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350°
for 50 to 55 minutes, or until a wooden pick
inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans, and let cool completely on wire racks.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together to form a ball.
Roll in nuts.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: health-full bran muffins
directions: Combine All-Bran, milk and molasses.
Let stand until most of the moisture is taken up.
Add egg and oil; beat well.
Stir in raisins.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add to wet mixture, stirring only until combined.

title: preacher's chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to
Grease
a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Beat together
sugars,
oleo and eggs.
Stir in milk.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into sugar mixture.
Stir in vanilla. Pour boiling water
over batter and stir in.
Pour batter into baking pan and
bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Ice with chocolate icing.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain well; mix all ingredients together. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Top with Parmesan and serve with melba toast.

title: mandy's brown sugar rounds
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg and mix well.
Mix in flour and soda.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Immediately remove from baking sheet.

title: chocolate peanut butter frosting
directions: Cook first seven ingredients until it boils and boil for two minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla. Cool in cold water, stirring until spreadable.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut middle out of bell peppers. Blanche bell peppers for 5 minutes. Brown hamburger meat, salt and pepper and onions. Cook rice separately. Add tomato sauce and rice to meat. Simmer for 10 minutes. Pour meat mixture in bell peppers. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Spread grated cheese on top of meat. Bake until cheese melts.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Blend the box of cake mix with the margarine and 1 egg.
Press the mixture into and up the sides of a cake pan.
Set aside enough powdered sugar to sprinkle on top of cake when finished.
Mix the remaining powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle the reserved powdered sugar on top of the cake.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Beat
eggs.
Add sugar, margarine, coconut, vanilla and vinegar; beat well.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until nice and brown.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Keep one slice of cheese to garnish.
Dice remaining cheese for loaf.
Also keep 1/4 cup of sauce to pour over loaf when in baking pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: gran gran's peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and butter and cook on low heat until reaches hard ball stage.
Drop in some cold water if it balls up it is ready.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Pour onto buttered dish and let firm.
Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: tollyho tomato pudding
directions: *You may substitute 1 quart of tomatoes, strained.

title: fried okra
directions: Cut okra into round pieces.
Season as desired.
Dip okra into an egg and milk mixture.
Dip into cornmeal.
Fry until brown and remove from pan.
Place on paper towel to drain excess oil.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased
casserole	pan.
Bake
for
45 minutes or a little longer, like 15 more minutes.

title: mom veda's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add flour and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix together Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese.
In separate bowl, mix together eggs, parsley, basil, oregano, salt, onion, Parmesan cheese and spaghetti sauce. Mix both batches together.
Place sauce on bottom of dish.
Stuff shells, place sauce on top.
Cook 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, eggs and slivered almonds together. Mix mayonnaise, chicken soup and lemon juice together.
Stir this mixture into salad portion.
Place in baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until it bubbles.
Top with crushed potato chips and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: apple and cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water. Let set slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Beat eggs; add to sausage with all other ingredients.
Place in greased casserole or shallow baking dish; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter and butterscotch clusters
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch chips in double boiler. Add to corn flakes.
Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper to cool.
Best stored in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal fudge cookies
directions: Stir together cocoa, sugar, milk and oleo
on stove until it comes to a boil.
Take off stove and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Dissolve peanut butter and add oats.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper and let set until hard.

title: pesto
directions: Place all ingredients in a food processor or in a blender; cover and process until smooth.
Makes 4 servings.
This sauce is great on almost any type of pasta.

title: la salsa alla genovere
directions: Put roast in pan; cover with chopped onions.
Add 2 bouillon cubes, margarine and water to cover meat.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Then uncover and cook onions down to sauce consistency, stirring frequently.
Use the sauce over pasta (mostaccioli are preferable).
Cook pasta; drain.
Add butter and some Parmesan also.
Put sauce over the top.
Use meat for second course with vegetable and salad.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and put into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheezy pastries
directions: Line bottom of greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan with one package of rolls.
Combine cheese, sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and juice.
Pour over dough.
Cover with remaining dough.
Brush top with beaten egg whites.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yields 12 to 16 pastries.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Take meat (drained) and add peas and carrots, dry Lipton soup, bouillon cubes and salt and pepper in pan and simmer until cubes have dissolved. Prepare instants as directed on package. Take meat mixture and place in a 9-inch square baking dish. Place mashed potatoes on top and spread evenly. Take cheese and spread on top. Place in an oven at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is browned. Feeds 3 to 4 people.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until yeast is dissolved.
Add 5 cups of the flour.
Beat with dough hook or spoon until batter is shiny and smooth.
Add remaining flour and blend well.
Pour the oil over the dough and knead until it all is absorbed (but not longer than 3 minutes).
Cover the bowl with waxed paper and a towel. Set in oven.
Turn oven to 150° and turn off in 5 minutes.
Leave oven door shut and let rise for 45 minutes, until double in bulk. Punch down.
Shape into 2 large or 3 medium loaves and place in buttered loaf pans.
Return to warm oven.
Let rise 30 minutes, until double.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool, covered.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
Fill a well-oiled dish with alternate layers of cabbage and then white sauce.
Cover with bread crumbs. Sprinkle with butter substitute.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rainbow salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Black cherry dissolved with 1 1/2 cups hot water; set.

title: cookie cutter sugar cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 350 degrees on ungreased cookie sheet for 6-8 minutes.

title: batter fried onion rings
directions: Sift flour, salt and pepper into bowl. Beat together egg yolks, beer and oil.
Add to flour mixture, stirring only until smooth.
Let stand for 1 hour. Slice onion 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick and separate into rings.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry and fold into batter.
Dip onions in batter, coating them thoroughly.
Heat oil (2-inches deep) and fry onions, without crowding, until brown on both sides. Drain.

title: o.j. flip
directions: Combine all ingredients in the blender and mix well.

title: fruit sauce
directions: Combine peaches, blueberries, apple juice and nutmeg in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove 2 tablespoons of liquid and combine with cornstarch.
Stir back into mixture.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for about 10 minutes.
Fold in strawberries and kiwi.
Serve warm over pancakes or waffles.
Yields 1 1/2 to 2 cups.

title: crispy sugar cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Roll out and use cookie cutters OR drop by rounded spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip the base of a drinking class in a small bowl of water, then in a small bowl of sugar, and flatten each cookie with the sugared glass.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned.
Cool.
When cool, they should be thin and crispy.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to package directions.
Drain. Add butter, cheese and whipping cream.
Mix well.
Add pepper and garlic to suit taste.
Serve hot.

title: caramels
directions: Melt margarine, then add brown sugar until blended.
Add milk and Karo syrup.
Stir constantly until it reaches soft ball stage. It will change color and start to pull away from side of pan. (You can use candy thermometer.)
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into greased pan and refrigerate.
Turn out onto cutting board.
Cut into pieces and wrap in wax paper.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Pour oil over crackers in a large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Pour over crackers and mix gently, but well.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour on a large cookie sheet.
Stir after the first 1/2 hour.
Let cool and stir from time to time during cooling.

title: seven-layer tex-mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Chop avocados and mix with the lemon juice, salt and pepper; spread on top of bean dip. Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, taco seasoning mix and picante sauce; spread on top of avocado mixture.
Next, spread chopped green onions.
Season tomatoes with seasoned salt to taste and spread on top of green onions.
Add chopped black olives.
Top off all layers with the shredded cheese.
Dip with tortilla chips.

title: chicken mulligatawny soup
directions: In saucepan, cook apple, coconut and onion with curry in butter until tender.
Add soup; pour into blender and blend until smooth. Return mixture to saucepan; gradually stir in milk and yogurt. Heat and stir occasionally.
Garnish with sliced apple.
Makes about 3 cups or 4 servings.

title: hot dogs(american hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Cook hot dogs.
Mix jam and mustard together.
Put hot dogs in the mixture.
Marinate overnight.
Heat and serve.

title: lei chiffon cake
directions: Beat until whites form very stiff peaks.
Mix about 1 cup of the egg white mixture into the flour mixture to lighten.
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over whipped egg whites, gently folding with rubber spatula just until blended.
Do not stir.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes in salted water.
Mash.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients and let stand awhile before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix coloring and cocoa; add coloring mixture to egg and beat well until blended.
Cook in 3 cake pans at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: potato soup
directions: Place potatoes in large saucepan; add cold water until just covered.
Add onion and celery.
Boil until potatoes are just tender.
Add garlic and pepper; boil until almost mushy.
Place cornstarch in a cup; add 1/2 cup very hot water.
Stir well.
Pour cornstarch mixture slowly into potato soup.
Stir constantly until thickened.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Add plenty of faith and mix well. Spread over a period of a lifetime and serve everybody you meet.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
When well mixed, shape into a ball and roll in the chopped pecans.

title: apple cheese pound cake(delicious during apple time!)
directions: Prepare pound cake as directed; pour into greased and floured spring-form pan.
Spread apple slices over cake top.
Sprinkle instant pudding over apples.
Combine cream cheese, eggs and sugar and spread over apples.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until brown.
Serve either warm or cold.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: buffet egg casserole
directions: Arrange buttered bread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut bread to cover entire pan.
Sprinkle cooked bacon over bread. Brown onion and sprinkle over bread, then the cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, pepper, salt and dry mustard.
Pour egg mixture over entire pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream and pat into 2 pizza pans or cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Watch closely so that it does not get too brown.
Cool.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
(Check after 1 hour.)

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in Bundt pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Spread cream cheese about 1/4-inch into small casserole dish. Cover
cream
cheese with boiled shrimp.
Pour cocktail sauce over shrimp to cover them.	Top with several shrimp and serve with crackers.

title: strawberry tossed salad
directions: Combine dressing in a jar and shake.

title: main dish pea soup
directions: Simmer ham hocks 2 hours and let stand.
Remove hocks from broth.
Let cool.
Remove fat from broth and meat from bones.
May be done day before making soup.

title: "putty" candy christmas treat
directions: Add first 4 ingredients.
Cook slowly, stirring until mixture "cracks" in cold water.
Remove from fire.
Add nuts, stirring constantly.
When cool, add vanilla.
When stiff, turn out on board, covered with cornstarch.
Knead and mold into loaves. Slice when ready to eat.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cook for 1 minute at a hard boil or until soft ball forms in cold water.
Let cool and beat with mixer.

title: minestrone soup(low-fat)
directions: Wash and sort beans.
Put in a large pan or Dutch oven with water.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes. Cover and let stand 1 hour.
In small skillet, cook onion, celery and garlic in chicken broth until onion is tender.
Add to beans with remainder of ingredients. Return to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll dough to 10 X 15 inch.
Cover dough with pepperoni and cheese.
Roll as jelly roll.
Seal edges and ends.
Melt margarine, oregano, and salt.
Brush bread.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.
Brush with margarine after bread is done.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix
flour,
shortening
and buttermilk.
Roll out in a long roll.
Place
sausage between wax paper and roll in same length as dough.
Place sausage on top of dough.
Roll like a jelly
roll. Place
in
freezer overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix and put in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out.
Cut and bake in moderate oven.

title: sex-in-a-pan
directions: Cut together flour, butter and walnuts and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; cool completely.
Blend together cream cheese and powdered sugar and add 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread over the flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly the chocolate and vanilla puddings; add milk.
Beat in mixer and spread over cream cheese-Cool Whip layer.
Spread 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip on top of pudding layer and sprinkle with chocolate shavings.

title: schnitz brod
directions: Cook
apples and
prunes,
separately;	let
cool.
Mix sugar, spices, salt,
Crisco
and molasses.
Dissolve yeast in some of the warm
water.
Mix
fruit,
raisins and nuts alternately with the flour.	(I
use
5 pounds of flour with 6 cups liquid in all, 3 cups
warm
water,
2 cups drained from fruit and rinsed out fruit
and	yeast dishes).	Knead dough and let stand to rise. Put in
greased bread pans.
Let rise.
Bake 1 hour at 400° for 15 minutes and at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 small loaves.

title: chinese vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingred. in bowl mixing well. Combine sugar and vinegar in bowl stirring to dissolve sugar. Pour over vegetables, tossing to mix. Chill overnight, stir occasionally. Yield 12 servings.

title: broccoli casserole(quick and easy microwave)
directions: Cook broccoli for 2 minutes on High in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Stir in 1/2 of the cheese and the other ingredients. Cook 5 minutes longer.

title: washday blues cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Bake in greased tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy microwave fudge
directions: Put sugar, cocoa and butter in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes. Stir and add 1/4 cup milk.
Don't use more milk.
Microwave 1 minute.
Stir and add vanilla and nuts if desired.
Put in buttered 9-inch pie plate and refrigerate.

title: corn light bread
directions: Grease pan with bacon drippings; pour excess drippings into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves in 9 x 5-inch pan.

title: different no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine. Bring to a rolling boil. Boil one minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Let cool.
Add marshmallows.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in large baking dish.
Pour rice over chicken. Sprinkle dry onion soup over rice.
Add golden mushroom soup and water.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: walnut toffee
directions: Butter a 9-inch square pan thoroughly. Spread the walnuts in the pan.
Mix together in heavy frypan the brown sugar and butter. Cook over medium heat (keep mixture bubbling), stirring constantly, for 12 minutes.
Pour toffee mixture quickly over nuts. Sprinkle the grated chocolate or chocolate bar over the hot toffee. Spread until smooth.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Chill and break into pieces.

title: lemon sauce
directions: In a saucepan, mix the sugar and flour well.
Add the water, egg and lemon juice to your taste.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat until thick.
This is good poured over gingerbread or spice cake.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, parsley, baking powder, and salt.
Mix milk and oil and pour into flour mixture.
Stir with a fork until combined.
Drop from a tablespoon into six mounds directly onto chicken (do not drop batter into liquid).
Cover; simmer about 12 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into dumplings comes out clean.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer chicken, dumplings and vegetables to a platter; cover.

title: chicken and water chestnut casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until fully done.
Debone and dice into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients, except dressing mix, together in a casserole dish and put aside.
Cook Stove Top dressing as directed on the box.
Top the casserole with the dressing and bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350 degrees.
